This measurement provides the total number of IP packets buffered. It is updated when downlink payload is buffered.

This measurement provides the total number of IP packets being buffered due to flow control. This counter is increased when buffering IP packets and the BSS Cell bucket is full; the BSS MS bucket is full; and when the BSS PFC bucket is full.

This measurement provides the number of discarded packets due to blocked BVCs. The counter is increased when a packet is discarded and the BSS has blocked a cell.
This measurement provides the number of discarded IP packets due to suspended mobile. This counter is increased when it is the MS that has suspended GPRS.
This measurement provides the number of incoming DOWNLOAD-BSS-PFC PDUs sent by the BSS.
This measurement provides the number of incoming Flow-Control-BVC PDUs sent by the BSS.
This measurement provides the number of incoming Flow-Control-MS PDUs sent by the BSS.
This measurement provides the number of incoming Flow-Control-PFC PDUs sent by the BSS.
This measurement provides the number of outgoing FLUSH-LL PDUs sent by the SGSN.
This measurement provides the number of incoming MODIFY-BSS-PFC PDUs sent by the BSS.
This measurement provides the number of incoming RADIO-STATUS PDUs sent by the BSS.
This measurement provides the number of outgoing PTP BVC-RESET PDUs sent by the SGSN.
This measurement provides the number of outgoing signaling BVC-RESET PDUs sent by the SGSN.

PmGroup.description: This PmGroup defines measurement types within the BSSGP_Nse area.

MeasurementType.description: This measurement provides the total number of downlink #BSSGP# octets per #NSE#.
This measurement provides the total number of downlink #BSSGP# packets per #NSE#.
This measurement provides the number of downlink #BSSGP# signalling packets per #NSE#.

This measurement provides the number of unknown #BVC# BSSGP-STATUS messages sent to the #BSC#. These messages are sent to the #BSC# when traffic, that is BSSGP-UL-UNITDATA messages, are received on the #PTP BVC#s that do not exist in the #SGSN-MME#. The traffic is then discarded. The #PTP BVC#s are non-existent in the #SGSN-MME# since no BVC-RESET messages, for the #PTP BVC#, have been received from the #BSC#. Action to be taken if the measurement exceeds its supervised threshold: Check the configuration. If no #PTP BVC# exists for incoming traffic it is probably because no BVC-RESET is received.
This measurement provides the total number of uplink #BSSGP# octets per #NSE#.
This measurement provides the total number of uplink #BSSGP# packets per #NSE#.
This measurement provides the number of uplink #BSSGP# signalling packets per #NSE#.

This measurement provides the total number of messages received from the remote peer on this connection.

This measurement provides the elapsed time, in seconds, since the last #BGP# UPDATE message was received from the peer. Each time the bgpPeerInUpdates counter is incremented the value of this object is set to zero. Action to be taken if the measurement exceeds its supervised threshold: A network failure might have occured in the network. Investigate if there are any problems with the #IP# connectivity at the interface board.
This measurement provides the number of #BGP# UPDATE messages received on this connection.
This measurement provides the total number of messages transmitted to the remote peer on this connection.
This measurement provides the number of #BGP# UPDATE messages transmitted on this connection.

MeasurementType.description: Total number of #CAMEL# dialogue attempts.

Incremented when it explicitly indicates in the message from gsmSCF that GPRS dialogue shall be terminated. This counter does not refer to any occurrence or event on application level, that is Release GPRS.

Incremented when 1) GPRS dialogue couldn't be established due to any reason, 2) it implicitly indicates in the message from gprsSSF that the GPRS dialogue is terminated, or, 3) gprsSSF implicitly terminates GPRS dialogue due to any internal reason (that is.resource shortage, overload protection, and so on). This counter does not refer to any occurrence or event on application level.

This measurement shows the number of A21-Event Notification messages sent by the MME to the IWS, including resendings.

This measurement shows the number of uplink A21-AIS messages sent by the MME to the IWS, including resendings.

PmGroup.description: This PmGroup defines measurement types within the Charging_GTPP area.

MeasurementType.description: This measurement provides the number of CDR transfer requests at the GTP Prime protocol that are sent for the first time from the SGSN to the CGF. It is incremented when the Data Record Transfer Request message is sent with the Packet Transfer Command IE having the value "Send Data Record Packet".

This measurement provides the number of CDR transfer requests at the GTP Prime protocol that are sent from the SGSN to the next CGF when the previous request could not be sent successfully. It is incremented when the Data Record Transfer Request message is sent with the Packet Transfer Command IE having the value "Send possible duplicated Data Record Packet".

This measurement provides the number of successful CDR packets transferred to the CGF. It is incremented when the Data Record Transfer Response message is received from the CGF with the Cause value "Request Accepted".

PmGroup.description: This PmGroup defines measurement types within the DNS area.

MeasurementType.description: This measurement provides the number of timed-out DNS queries where no response is received from any DNS server after retransmissions. #Note: The DNS query succeeds, if the DNS record is cached in the SGSN-MME. This is because the SGSN-MME indefinitely reuses the cached record when there is a timeout, even though the time-to-live value is exceeded.# Action to be taken if the measurement exceeds its supervised threshold: For more information on how to troubleshoot DNS connectivity, see DNS Related Faults in Troubleshooting. The consequences of lost DNS connectivity are as follows: - DNS queries fail if the record is not cached. This can lead to major service outage. - DNS queries succeed if the record is cached, even after the record expires (time-to-live value exceeded). - All DNS queries fail as soon as the DNS cache is cleared. The DNS cache is cleared by a restart or an operator command. - DNS server provisioning does not have any effect until the DNS connectivity is restored.

MeasurementType.description: This measurement provides the number of octets in incoming #GTP# data packets on the Gn interface without the #GTP# header. Note that the counter includes the total number of #GTP# packets sent, regardless of the #GTP# version. While the counter counts octets, the measurement unit of reported value is KOctets (1024 octets).

This measurement provides the number of octets in incoming #GTP# data packets on the S4 interface. #Note: The counter includes the total number of #GTP# packets sent, regardless of the #GTP# version. While the counter counts octets, the measurement unit of reported value is KOctets (1024 octets).Note#

This measurement provides the number of #GTP# data #PDUs# which have been accepted and processed by the #GTP# entity on the Gn interface. Note that the counter includes the total number of #GTP# packets sent, regardless of the #GTP# version.

This measurement provides the number of #GTP# data #PDU#s which have been accepted and processed by the #GTP# entity on the S4 interface. #Note: The counter includes the total number of #GTP# packets sent, regardless of the #GTP# version.Note#

This measurement provides the number of octets in outgoing #GTP# data packets on the Gn interface without the #GTP# header. Note that the counter includes the total number of #GTP# packets sent, regardless of the #GTP# version. While the counter counts octets, the measurement unit of reported value is KOctets (1024 octets).

This measurement provides the number of octets in outgoing #GTP# data packets on the S4 interface. #Note: The counter includes the total number of #GTP# packets sent, regardless of the #GTP# version. While the counter counts octets, the measurement unit of reported value is KOctets (1024 octets).Note#

This measurement provides the number of #GTP# data #PDUs# which have been generated by the #GTP# protocol entity on the Gn interface. Note that the counter includes the total number of #GTP# packets sent, regardless of the #GTP# version.

This measurement provides the number of #GTP# data #PDU#s which have been generated by the #GTP# protocol entity on the S4 interface. #Note: The counter includes the total number of #GTP# packets sent, regardless of the #GTP# version.Note#

This measurement provides the number of incoming #GTP# data packets where payload length indicated in #GTP# header is inconsistent with actual length. The counter includes the total number of #GTP# packets sent, regardless of the #GTP# version.

Note#

This measurement shall in the normal case correspond to the #frPvcTxFrames# measurement type. A discrepancy between these two measurements may indicate a faulty configuration or an overload condition.
This measurement provides the number of discarded packets in the #NS# layer due to congestion in the upper layer of the Frame Relay stack.

PmGroup.description: This PmGroup defines measurement types within the GeographicallyRedundantPool area.

MeasurementType.description: This measurement provides the number of attempted PS paging procedures initiated by the MME for Network Triggered Service Restoration (NTSR). The counter is incremented when a PS paging procedure is started upon receipt of the Downlink Data Notification message from the SGW with IMSI. The counter is incremented at the sending of the paging message with the current S-TMSI in the procedure.
This measurement provides the number of the received Downlink Data Notification (DDN) messages with IMSI. This counter is incremented each time a DDN message with IMSI is received from the SGW.

This measurement provides the number of successful Downlink Data Notification Acknowledge with IMSI. This counter is incremented each time a Downlink Data Notification Acknowledge message with IMSI and the cause "Request accepted" is sent out.

This measurement provides the number of S6a messages blocked due to the Attach Throttling function in the geographically redundant pool . The counter is incremented when an S6a message is blocked because the number of messages under throttling control exceeds the threshold configured by the MMEAttachThrottlingAttachRateLimit parameter.

This measurement provides the number of UE geo-replica creation messages received. This counter is incremented each time the Replication MME receives an Echo Request message over the S10 interface with the operation code "Backup Required".

This measurement provides the number of UE geo-replica creation messages sent . This counter is incremented each time the Serving MME sends Echo Request message over the S10 interface with the operation code "Backup Required".

This measurement provides the number of UE geo-replica deletion messages received. This counter is incremented each time the Replication MME receives an Echo Request message over the S10 interface with the operation code "Delete Required".

This measurement provides the number of UE geo-replica deletion messages sent. This counter is incremented each time the Serving MME sends Echo Request message over the S10 interface with the operation code "Delete Required".

This measurement provides the number of UE geo-replica retrieval attempts. This counter is incremented when the new MME trying to restore the UE service sends one or multiple Echo Request messages over the S10 interface with the operation code "Retrieval Request". The multiple retrieval messages are counted as one attempt.

This measurement provides the number of all Retrieval messages sent by the new MME. This counter is incremented each time the new MME sends an Echo Request message over the S10 interface with the operation code "Retrieval Request". For one UE geo-replica retrieval attempt, multiple retrieval messages may be sent to different MMEs in the pool and they are all counted.

This measurement provides the number of successful UE geo-replica retrievals. This counter is incremented when the new MME trying to restore the UE service receives the successful Echo Response message over the S10 interface with the operation code "Retrieval Response".

This measurement provides the total number of #ICMP# messages received on all logical networks located on the entity. Note that this counter also includes some of the messages counted by the icmpInErrors counter, such as bad code and bad length messages.
This measurement provides the number of #ICMP# Parameter Problem messages received on all logical networks on the entity.

PmGroup.description: This PmGroup defines measurement types within the IPInterface area.

MeasurementType.description: This measurement provides the number of inbound packets that have been dropped due to lack of resources or denied by packet filtering. Lack of resources can for example be when packet queues are full, the driver is out of buffers, clusters or descriptors. This counter is applicable to packets forwarded in Ethernet frames, which can include IPv4 packets, IPv6 packets, and ARP packets.

This measurement provides the total number of octets received on the interface, including framing characters. This counter is applicable to packets forwarded in Ethernet frames, which can include IPv4 packets, IPv6 packets, and ARP packets.

This measurement provides the total number of packets, delivered by this sub-layer to a higher (sub-)layer. This counter is applicable to packets forwarded in Ethernet frames, which can include IPv4 packets, IPv6 packets, and ARP packets.

This measurement provides the number of outbound packets that have been dropped due to lack of resources or denied by packet filtering. There can be a lack of resources when packet queues are full, or when the driver is out of buffers, clusters or descriptors. This counter is applicable to packets forwarded in Ethernet frames, which can include IPv4 packets, IPv6 packets, and ARP packets.

This measurement provides the total number of octets transmitted out of the interface, including framing characters. This counter is applicable to packets forwarded in Ethernet frames, which can include IPv4 packets, IPv6 packets, and ARP packets.

This measurement provides the total number of packets that higher-level protocols requested to be transmitted. This counter is applicable to packets forwarded in Ethernet frames, which can include IPv4 packets, IPv6 packets, and ARP packets.

This measurement provides the length of the output packet queue, in packets. Action to be taken if the measurement exceeds its supervised threshold: The severity of the overload depends on the queue's length (the threshold value) and the overload frequency. If the threshold is reached often, it may indicate that either the network capacity or the load sharing needs to be improved. This counter is applicable to packets forwarded in Ethernet frames, which can include IPv4 packets, IPv6 packets, and ARP packets.

Number of packets classified as #IPsec# or GRE by filter on this slot. The counter value is only applicable for #IBAS# #IP# Interface PIUs.

PmGroup.description: This PmGroup defines measurement types within the IP_PIU area. The measurements only applies to IPv4 packets.

MeasurementType.description: This measurement provides the number of input datagrams for which this entity is not the final IPv4 destination, and so an attempt is made to find a route to forward the input datagrams to the IPv4 destination. This measurement counts IP packets that include payload, signalling, and dynamic routing packets.

This measurement provides the number of #IP# datagram fragments that have been generated as a result of fragmentation at the logical networks on this entity. This measurement counts payload, signalling, and dynamic routing.

This measurement provides the number of #IP# datagrams that have been discarded because they needed to be fragmented at logical networks on this entity but could not be because, for example, their Don't Fragment flag was set. This measurement counts payload, signalling, and dynamic routing.
This measurement provides the number of #IP# datagrams that have been successfully fragmented at all logical networks on this entity. This measurement counts payload, signalling, and dynamic routing.

This measurement provides the number of input datagrams discarded on the logical networks on this entity, because the #IP# address in their #IP# header's destination field was not a valid address. This count includes invalid addresses (for example, 0.0.0.0) and addresses of unsupported classes (for example, Class E). This measurement counts payload, signalling, and dynamic routing.

This measurement provides the number of input datagrams discarded on all logical networks on this entity. This due to errors in their #IP# headers, i.e. version number mismatch, bad header length, bad #IP# total length. In addition, for packets destinated to a router board, errors discovered in processing control flags, header checksum, and #IP# options are counted. This measurement counts payload, signalling, and dynamic routing.

This measurement provides the total number of input datagrams received from interfaces, including those received in error. This measurement counts IP packets that include payload, signalling, and dynamic routing packets.

This measurement provides the number of #IP# datagrams discarded, on all logical networks on this entity, because no route could be found to transmit them to their destination. Note that this counter includes any packets counted in the ipForwDatagrams counter which meets this no-route criterion. This measurement counts payload, signalling, and dynamic routing.

This measurement provides the number of failures (for any reason) detected by the #IP# reassembly algorithm for all logical networks on this entity. Note that this is not necessarily a count of discarded #IP# fragments. This measurement is not used for payload traffic, only for traffic terminating on the router board.

This measurement provides the number of #IP# datagrams successfully reassembled on all logical networks on this entity. This measurement is not used for payload traffic, only for traffic terminating on the router board.

This measurement provides the number of #IP# fragments received, for all logical networks on this entity, which needed to be reassembled at this entity. This measurement is not used for payload traffic, only for traffic terminating on the router board.

PmGroup.description: This PmGroup defines measurement types within the IP_RouterInstance area. The measurements only applies to IPv4 packets.

MeasurementType.description: This measurement provides the number of input datagrams for which this entity is not the final IPv4 destination, and so an attempt is made to find a route to forward the input datagrams to the IPv4 destination. This measurement counts IP packets that include payload, signalling, and dynamic routing packets.

This measurement provides the number of routes currently in the forwarding table. The #SGSN-MME# allows a maximum of 5000 routes in the forwarding table. Exceeding this limit is at the risk of the operator and might cause loss of connectivity. If PEB/SCXB-based routing is used, total loss of IP connectivity will be experienced (for that network).;This measurement type is indexed by #IP# indexing option 2, MagId.SlotId.Network only. Action to be taken if the measurement exceeds its supervised threshold: If the size supported by the #SGSN-MME# has been exceeded, then a degradation of #IP# connectivity for traffic leaving the #SGSN-MME# may be experienced. If PEB/SCXB-based routing is used, total loss of IP connectivty will be experienced (for that network). Corrective measures include reducing the number of static routes configured on the router #PIU#, or reducing the number of routes exported to the #SGSN-MME# from external routers. If OSPF is used, consider using OSPF NSSA to reduce the number of routes.

This measurement provides the number of #IP# datagram fragments that have been generated as a result of fragmentation at the indexed logical network. This measurement counts payload, signalling, and dynamic routing.

This measurement provides the number of #IP# datagrams that have been discarded because they needed to be fragmented at the indexed logical network but could not be because, for example, their Don't Fragment flag was set. This measurement counts payload, signalling, and dynamic routing.
This measurement provides the number of #IP# datagrams that have been successfully fragmented at the indexed logical network. This measurement counts payload, signalling, and dynamic routing.

This measurement provides the number of input datagrams discarded on the indexed logical network, because the #IP# address in their #IP# header's destination field was not a valid address. This count includes invalid addresses (for example, 0.0.0.0) and addresses of unsupported classes (for example, Class E). This measurement counts payload, signalling, and dynamic routing.

This measurement provides the number of input datagrams discarded on all logical networks on this entity. This due to errors in their #IP# headers, i.e. version number mismatch, bad header length, bad #IP# total length. In addition, for packets destinated to a router board, errors discovered in processing control flags, header checksum, and #IP# options are counted. This measurement counts payload, signalling, and dynamic routing.

This measurement provides the number of input datagrams received on the indexed logical network, including those received in error. This measurement counts IP packets that include payload, signalling, and dynamic routing packets.

This measurement provides the number #IP# datagrams discarded, on the indexed logical network, because no route could be found to transmit them to their destination. Note that this counter includes any packets counted in the ipForwDatagrams counter which meets this no-route criterion. This measurement counts payload, signalling, and dynamic routing.

This measurement provides the number of failures (for any reason) detected by the #IP# reassembly algorithm for the indexed logical network. Note that this is not necessarily a count of discarded #IP# fragments. This measurement is not used for payload traffic, only for traffic terminating on the router board.

This measurement provides the number of #IP# datagrams successfully reassembled on the indexed logical network. This measurement is not used for payload traffic, only for traffic terminating on the router board.

This measurement provides the number of #IP# fragments received on the indexed logical network which needed to be reassembled at this entity. This measurement is not used for payload traffic, only for traffic terminating on the router board.

MeasurementType.description: This measurement provides the number of bytes transferred on this #SA# so far. Note: This counter is only applicable to MkVI and MkVI+.
This measurement provides the number of incorrect packets processed associated with the current #SA#. Note: This counter is only applicable to MkVI and MkVI+.
This measurement provides the number of correct packets processed associated with the current #SA#. Note: This counter is only applicable to MkVI and MkVI+.

PmGroup.description: This PmGroup defines measurement types within the IPsec_PIU area.

MeasurementType.description: This measurement provides the number of #IPsec# and #GRE# packets discarded in the #IPsec# engine. Action to be taken if the measurement exceeds it's supervised threshold: Check the available #IPsec# and #GRE# measurement types. Most probably, an #SA# has not been set up as it should, either locally or on the sending side. Note: This counter is only applicable to MkVI and MkVI+.

This measurement provides the number of incoming #IPsec# and #GRE# packets for which no configuration is found in #SADB#. Action to be taken if the measurement exceeds its supervised threshold: Check the #IPsec# and #GRE# configuration. Most probably, an #SA# has not been set up as it should, either locally or on the sending side. Note: This counter is only applicable to MkVI and MkVI+.
This measurement provides the number of #IPsec# or #GRE# packets which has been processed correctly, coming in. Note: This counter is only applicable to MkVI and MkVI+.

This measurement provides the number of times the comparison between the given value and the calculated (with md5 algorithm) value did not match. Action to be taken if the measurement exceeds its supervised threshold: Check the #IPsec# configuration. Most probably the wrong authentication keys for one or more #SA#s are used. Many forms of data corruption, that is bit errors in the packets, can also cause the authentication to fail. Note: This counter is only applicable to MkVI and MkVI+.
This measurement provides the number of #IPsec# and #GRE# packets which has been processed correctly, going out. Note: This counter is only applicable to MkVI and MkVI+.

This measurement provides the number of times the comparison between the given value and the calculated (through the sha1 algorithm) value did not match. Action to be taken if the measurement exceeds its supervised threshold: Check the #IPsec# configuration. Most probably the wrong authentication keys for one or more #SA#s are used. Many forms of data corruption, that is, bit errors in the packets, can also cause the authentication to fail. Note: This counter is only applicable to MkVI and MkVI+.

This measurement provides the number of #IPsec# and #GRE# header events. The counter is incremented by one every time an #IPsec# or #GRE# header is added or removed. Note: This counter is only applicable to MkVI and MkVI+.

PmGroup.description: This PmGroup defines measurement types within the IPv4v6_PIU area.

MeasurementType.description: This measurement shows how many percent of the total number of available host routes in the IP Interface PIU L3 switching HW that are currently utilized (for all VPNs). This is applicable for both IPv4 and IPv6 since they share the same HW resource. When the HW routing table is full, outbound traffic may be forwarded in SW which leads to a lower forwarding capacity. Action to be taken if the measurement exceeds its supervised threshold: To minimize the number of routes and to decrease the HW table utilization, it is recommended to use OSPF NSSA or route aggregation in the site routers.

This measurement shows how many percent of the total number of available network routes in the IP Interface PIU L3 switching HW that are currently utilized (for all VPNs). This is applicable for both IPv4 and IPv6 since they share the same HW resource. When the HW routing table is full, outbound traffic may be forwarded in SW which leads to a lower forwarding capacity. Action to be taken if the measurement exceeds its supervised threshold: To minimize the number of routes and to decrease the HW table utilization, it is recommended to use OSPF NSSA or route aggregation in the site routers.

This measurement provides the number of input #IPv6# datagrams discarded on all logical networks on this entity because the #IP# address in their #IP# header's destination field was valid. This measurement type is indexed by either of the indexing options. This measurement counts signaling IPv6 packets.

This measurement provides the number of input #IPv6# datagrams discarded on all logical networks on this entity, due to errors in their #IP# headers. This includes version number mismatch, other format errors, hop count exceeded, errors discovered in processing their #IP# options, etc. This measurement type is indexed by either of the indexing options. This measurement counts signaling IPv6 packets.
This measurement provides the total number of input #IPv6# datagrams received from interfaces, including those received in errors. This measurement counts signaling IPv6 packets.

This measurement provides the number of input #IPv6# datagrams discarded on all logical networks on this entity because the datagram frame didn't carry enough data. This measurement type is indexed by either of the indexing options.

This measurement provides the number of locally generated #IPv6# datagrams discarded on all logical networks on this entity because no route could be found to transmit them to their destination. This measurement type is indexed by either of the indexing options. This measurement counts signaling IPv6 packets.

This measurement provides the number of IPv6 routes currently in the forwarding table. The #SGSN-MME# allows a maximum of 120 routes in the forwarding table of each IP network. Exceeding this limit is at the risk of the operator and causes loss of connectivity. For PEB/SCXB-based routing, exceeding the limit results in total loss of IP connectivity (for that network). This measurement type is indexed by #IP# indexing option 2, MagId.SlotId.Network only. Action to be taken if the measurement exceeds its supervised threshold: Corrective measures include reducing the number of static routes configured on the IP Interface #PIU#.

This measurement provides the number of input #IPv6# datagrams discarded on all logical networks on this entity because the #IP# address in their #IP# header's destination field was not valid. This measurement type is indexed by either of the indexing options. This measurement counts signaling IPv6 packets.

This measurement provides the number of input #IPv6# datagrams discarded on all logical networks on this entity, due to errors in their #IP# headers. This includes version number mismatch, other format errors, hop count exceeded, errors discovered in processing their #IP# options, etc. This measurement type is indexed by either of the indexing options. This measurement counts signaling IPv6 packets.
This measurement provides the total number of input #IPv6# datagrams received from interfaces, including those received in errors. This measurement counts signaling IPv6 packets.

This measurement provides the number of input #IPv6# datagrams discarded on all logical networks on this entity because the datagram frame didn't carry enough data. This measurement type is indexed by either of the indexing options.

This measurement provides the number of locally generated #IPv6# datagrams discarded on all logical networks on this entity because no route could be found to transmit them to their destination. This measurement type is indexed by either of the indexing options. This measurement counts signaling IPv6 packets.

MeasurementType.description: This measurement provides the number of automatic connection restarts. The counter is incremented when an error is detected in the software which handles a single subscriber (#MS#) and results in an automatic connection restart. Action to be taken if the measurement exceeds its supervised threshold: This is an indication of a high rate of automatic connection restarts of a single subscriber. Only if this continues over a longer period of time, there is need to further investigate the cause.

This measurement provides the number of manually deleted subscribers. The counter is incremented when an operator manually deletes a subscriber, that is, an #MS# by using the #delete_subscriber# CLI command.

MeasurementType.description: The number of attached mobiles lost due to any crash or restart except node restart and large restart. The measurement is collected and aggregated periodically. The accuracy may therefore be affected at repeated restarts.

This measurement provides the number of attempted location service request procedures in the #SGSN-MME#. Trigger: Sending the LCS-AP Location Request message to the #E-SMLC# over the SLs interface.
This measurement provides the number of attempted location service request procedures in the #SGSN#. Trigger: Sending the BSSGP Perform Location Request message to the #BSS# over the Gb interface.

This measurement provides the number of successful location service request procedures in the #SGSN-MME#. Trigger: Reception of the LCS-AP Location Response message from the #E-SMLC# over the SLs interface with a successful result.
This measurement provides the number of successful location service request procedures in the #SGSN#. Trigger: Reception of the Perform Location Response message from the #BSS# over the Gb interface.

This measurement provides the number of successful location service request procedures in the #SGSN#. Trigger: Reception of the RANAP Location Report message from the #RNC# over the Iu interface with a successful result.
This measurement provides the number of attempted #MT-LR# procedures in the #SGSN#. Trigger: Reception of a ProvideSubscriberLocation Request message from the #GMLC# over the Lg interface.
This measurement provides the number of attempted SLg #MT-LR# procedures in the #SGSN-MME#. Trigger: Reception of a Provide Subscriber Location Request message from the #GMLC# over the SLg interface.

This measurement provides the number of successful #MT-LR# procedures in the #SGSN#. The procedure is considered successful when the #RAN# has provided an estimation of the MS's location. Trigger: Sending the ProvideSubscriberLocation Response message to the #GMLC# over the Lg interface with a successful result code.

This measurement provides the number of successful #MT-LR# procedures in the #SGSN-MME#. The procedure is considered successful when the #E-SMLC# has provided an estimation of the UE's location. Trigger: Sending the Provide Subscriber Location Response message to the #GMLC# over the SLg interface with a successful result code.
This measurement provides the number of attempted SLg #NI-LR# procedures in the #SGSN-MME#. Trigger: Sending the Subscriber Location Report message to the #GMLC# over the SLg interface.

This measurement provides the number of successful #NI-LR# procedures in the #SGSN-MME#. Trigger: Reception of the Subscriber Location Report Ack message from the #GMLC# with a successful result code.

PmGroup.description: This PmGroup defines measurement types within the LocationServices_G area.

MeasurementType.description: This measurement provides the number of attempted paging procedures due to the location service. The counter is incremented when a paging procedure is started due to location service, that is at the transmission of the first paging message in the procedure. The paging procedure consists of one or more paging messages with the current P-TMSI, optionally followed by paging messages with the old P-TMSI. A new set of paging messages, triggered by a new location service from a GMLC is regarded as a new procedure. Paging with IMSI (due to abnormal situation) is also regarded as a new procedure.

This measurement provides the number of successful paging procedures initiated due to location service, irrespective of the paging being an initial paging request or resending of the paging request. This counter is incremented each time a paging procedure, due to location service, is successfully concluded.

PmGroup.description: This PmGroup defines measurement types within the LocationServices_U area.

MeasurementType.description: This measurement provides the number of attempted location service request procedures in the #SGSN#. Trigger: Sending the RANAP Location Reporting Control message to the #RNC# over the Iu interface.

This measurement provides the number of attempted paging procedures due to the location service. The counter is incremented when a paging procedure is started due to location service, that is at the transmission of the first paging message in the procedure. The paging procedure consists of one or more paging messages with the current P-TMSI, optionally followed by paging messages with the old P-TMSI. A new set of paging messages, triggered by a new location service from a GMLC is regarded as a new procedure. Paging with IMSI (due to abnormal situation) is also regarded as a new procedure.

This measurement provides the number of successful paging procedures initiated due to location service, irrespective of the paging being an initial paging request or resending of the paging request. This counter is incremented each time a paging procedure, due to location service, is successfully concluded.

PmGroup.description: This PmGroup defines measurement types within the LogicalLinkControl_G area.

MeasurementType.description: This measurement provides the number of erroneously received #LLC# frames in case of error detection in the #SGSN# (uplink transmission, #SGSN#).
This measurement provides the number of #LLC# frames ciphered using #GEA1# algorithm.
This measurement provides the number of #LLC# frames ciphered using #GEA2# algorithm.
This measurement provides the number of #LLC# frames ciphered using #GEA3# algorithm.
This measurement provides the number of #LLC# frames deciphered using #GEA1# algorithm.
This measurement provides the number of #LLC# frames deciphered using #GEA2# algorithm.
This measurement provides the number of #LLC# frames deciphered using #GEA3# algorithm.
This measurement provides the number of received #LLC# frames by the #SGSN#.
This measurement provides the number of #LLC# frames sent by the #SGSN#.

PmGroup.description: This PmGroup defines measurement types within the MBMS area.

MeasurementType.description: This measurement provides the number of active MBMS sessions in this #SGSN#.

PmGroup.description: This PmGroup defines measurement types within the MSCPool area.

MeasurementType.description: This measurement provides the current number of Gs associated subscribers per #MSC# within this #SGSN#.

PmGroup.description: This PmGroup defines measurement types within the Mobility_G area.

MeasurementType.description: This measurement provides the number of attempt of combined #GPRS#/#IMSI# attach procedures initiated within this #SGSN# area. Both sendings and resendings from #MSs# are counted.
This measurement provides the number of attempted Combined #GPRS#/#IMSI# detach procedures #MS#-initiated within this #SGSN# area. Both sendings and resendings from #MSs# are counted.
This measurement provides the number of attempted #GPRS# attach procedures initiated within this #SGSN# area. Resendings from #MSs# are also counted.
MeasurementType.alarmRaiseDefaultLevel: value of 1% of attach limit (hard limit)
MeasurementType.alarmClearDefaultLevel: value of 0.5% of attach limit (hard limit)

MeasurementType.description: This measurement provides the number of attempted #GPRS# attach procedures, within this #SGSN# area, initiated by visiting #GPRS# subscribers . Visiting subscribers are defined by the roaming status parameter in the #IMSI# number series configuration. Resendings from #MSs# are not counted.
MeasurementType.alarmRaiseDefaultLevel: value of 0.2% of attach limit (hard limit)
MeasurementType.alarmClearDefaultLevel: value of 0.1% of attach limit (hard limit)

MeasurementType.description: This measurement provides the number of attempted #GPRS# detach procedures within this #SGSN# area. Resendings from #MSs# are also counted.

This measurement provides the number of attempted #GPRS# detach procedures initiated by #SGSN#. The counter is incremented when sending Detach Request to an #MS#. The counter is not incremented when resending Detach Request to the #MS#.
This measurement provides the number of attempted #IMSI# detach procedures #MS#-initiated within this #SGSN# area. Both sendings and resendings from #MSs# are counted.

This measurement provides the number of attempted inter-#SGSN# #RA# Update procedures initiated in this #SGSN#, where the old #RA# is served by another #SGSN#. Both sendings and resending from #MSs# are also counted.
MeasurementType.alarmRaiseDefaultLevel: value of 1% of attach limit (hard limit)
MeasurementType.alarmClearDefaultLevel: value of 0.5% of attach limit (hard limit)

MeasurementType.description: This measurement provides the number of attempted inter-SGSN #RAU# procedures initiated by visiting #GPRS# subscribers within this #SGSN#, where the old #RA# is served by another #SGSN#. Visiting subscribers are defined by the roaming status parameter in the #IMSI# number series configuration. Resendings from #MSs# are not counted.
MeasurementType.alarmRaiseDefaultLevel: value of 0.2% of attach limit (hard limit)
MeasurementType.alarmClearDefaultLevel: value of 0.1% of attach limit (hard limit)

MeasurementType.description: This measurement provides the number of attempted intra-SGSN #RA# update procedures initiated within this #SGSN# area. Both sendings and resending from #MSs# are counted. All types of intra-SGSN #RA# Update requests are counted: normal #RA# update, periodic #RA# update and #RA# update acting as resume of a suspended #MS#. The intra-SGSN #ISC# procedures are not included in this measurement.
This measurement provides the aggregation of the MM.AttPsPagingProcGb measurement types.
The discardedAttachMsError counter is incremented when there is a rejected attach because the #MS# has wrong #TLLI#. There is an #IMSI# attach on non-random #TLLI#.

This measurement provides the number of discarded combined attach requests on #DP# level, due to overload protection or incorrect information elements. For information about the possible reject causes, refer to the Cause Codes and Events document.
This measurement provides the number of discarded combined routing area update requests on #DP# level, due to overload protection or incorrect information elements.
This measurement provides the number of discarded detach requests on #DP# level, due to overload protection or incorrect information elements.

This measurement provides the number of discarded attach requests on #DP# level, due to overload protection or incorrect information elements. #GPRS# attach and GPRS attach with #IMSI# already attached
This measurement provides the number of discarded payload #PDUs# on #DP# level, due to overload protection or incorrect information elements.
This measurement provides the number of discarded routing area update requests on #DP# level, due to overload protection or incorrect information elements

This measurement provides the number of attempted paging procedures initiated at the #SGSN# over the Gb interface. The counter is incremented when a paging procedure is started, that is at the transmission of the first paging message in the procedure. The #PS# paging procedure consists of one or more paging messages with the current #P-TMSI#, optionally followed by paging messages with the old #P-TMSI#. A new set of paging messages, triggered by a new #DL# #PDU#, is regarded as a new procedure. Paging with #IMSI# (due to abnormal situation) is also regarded as a new procedure. This measurement counts both #CS# and #PS# paging procedures. Note that there is no repetition for #CS# paging, hence each #CS# paging message is counted as one procedure.

Number of Attach or Inter-#SGSN# #RA#-update requests that were rejected by admission control. The request is rejected and fault code 22 is sent to the #MS#, indicating congestion. The admission control reject is caused by maximum #SAU# limit reached.
This measurement provides the aggregation of the MM.SuccPsPagingProcGb measurement types.

This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful attach request per #SGSN-MME#, that is, whenever an attach reject message is sent. Action to be taken if the measurement exceeds its supervised threshold: This is an indication of high attach failure rates, typically caused by a decision not to allow #GPRS# usage for some subscriber categories. To find out if there are real problems, subtract the unsuccessful attaches due to cause code 7 (#GPRS# not allowed), cause code 8 (#GPRS# services and non-#GPRS# services not allowed) and cause code 14 (#GPRS# services not allowed in this #PLMN#). If the attach failure rate remains on a high failure rate, continue the troubleshooting by checking the #SS7# network.
This measurement provides the number of subscribers in READY state within this #SGSN# area.
This measurement provides the number of subscribers in STANDBY state within this #SGSN# area.

This measurement provides the number of successfully completed of Combined #GPRS#/#IMSI# attach procedures initiated within this #SGSN# area. The counter is not incremented when resending Attach Accept to the #MS#. If the #IMSI# (CS) Attach failed but the #GPRS# Attach was successful, no counters are incremented.

This measurement provides the number of successfully performed #GPRS# attach procedures within this #SGSN# area. The counter is not incremented when resending Attach Accept to the #MS#. If an Attach Request indicating Combined #GPRS#/#IMSI# Attach was received and the #IMSI# (CS) Attach failed but the #GPRS# Attach was successful, the counter is not incremented.

This measurement provides the number of successfully performed #GPRS# attach procedures within this #SGSN# area, initiated by visiting #GPRS# subscribers. Visiting subscribers are defined by the roaming status parameter in the #IMSI# number series configuration. If the SGSN resends an Attach Accept message to the #MS#, the counter is not incremented. If the SGSN receives an Attach Request message indicating Combined #GPRS# or #IMSI# Attach and the #IMSI# (CS) Attach did fail whereas the #GPRS# Attach was successful, the counter is not incremented.

This measurement provides the number of successfully completed #GPRS# detach procedures #SGSN#-initiated within this #SGSN# area. The procedure is not considered successful if Detach Accept is not received, even though the #MS# is detached in the network.
This measurement provides the number of successfully completed inter-#SGSN# #RA# Update procedures in this #SGSN#.

This measurement provides the number of successfully completed inter-SGSN #RAU# procedures initiated by visiting #GPRS# subscribers within this #SGSN# area. Visiting subscribers are defined by the roaming status parameter in the #IMSI# number series configuration.

This measurement provides the number of successfully performed intra-SGSN #RA# update procedures initiated in this #SGSN#. The counter is not stepped when resending #RA# update "accept". All types of intra-SGSN #RA# update requests are counted: normal #RA# update, periodic #RA# update and #RA# update acting as resume of a suspended #MS#. The intra-SGSN #ISC# procedures are not included in this measurement.

This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful packet switched paging procedures over the Gb interface within this #SGSN-MME# area, that is, packet switching paging procedures that are re-started when the previous attempt has timed out. The counter is incremented when a #PS# paging procedure has failed, that is, at timeout after transmission of the last paging message in the procedure. The paging procedure consists of one or more paging messages with the current #P-TMSI#, optionally followed by paging messages with the old #P-TMSI#. A new set of paging messages, triggered by a new #DL# PDU, is regarded as a new procedure. Note that the total number of attempts minus successful attempts is not the same as unsuccessful due to discarded messages and re-sendings of messages. Action to be taken if the measurement exceeds its supervised threshold: This is an indication of high paging failure rates, typically caused by lack of radio coverage. Continue the troubleshooting in the radio network.

PmGroup.description: This PmGroup defines measurement types within the Mobility_HO_E area.

MeasurementType.description: This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful intra-MME S1-based Handover procedures that have failed due to Roaming Restrictions.
This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful intra-MME S1-based Handover procedures that have failed due to Regional Subscription.
This measurement provides the number of attempted Handover procedures over the S1 interface. The counter is incremented when the Handover Request arrives at the source MME.
This measurement provides the number of attempted Handover procedures over the S1 interface. The counter is incremented when Forward Relocation Request arrives at the target MME.

This measurement provides the number of successful Inter MME Handover procedures over the S1 interface. The counter is incremented when the Forward Relocation Complete Notification arrives at the source MME from the target MME.
This measurement provides the number of successful Inter MME Handover procedures over the S1 interface. The counter is incremented when the Handover Notify message arrives at the target MME.
This measurement provides the number of attempted X2-based Handover procedures. Trigger: Receiving the S1-AP Path Switch Request message from the target eNodeB.
This measurement provides the number of failed X2-based Handover procedures. Trigger: Sending the S1-AP Path Switch Request Failure message to the target eNodeB.
This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful X2-based Handover procedures that have failed due to Roaming Restrictions.
This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful X2-based Handover procedures that have failed due to Regional Subscription.
This measurement provides the number of successful X2-based Handover procedures. Trigger: Sending the S1-AP Path Switch Request Acknowledge message to the target eNodeB.
MeasurementType.supervisionDefaultInterval: This measurement provides the number of successful X2-based Handover without SGW relocation procedures. Trigger: Sending of S1-AP Path Switch Request Acknowledge message to the target eNodeB. This measurement provides the number of successful X2-based Handover without SGW relocation procedures. Trigger: Sending of S1-AP Path Switch Request Acknowledge message to the target eNodeB. N/A

PmGroup.description: This PmGroup defines measurement types within the Mobility_IRATHO_E area.

MeasurementType.description: This measurement provides the number of successful intra-SGSN/MME #IRAT# #PS# handover procedures from #UMTS# access to #LTE# access. The counter increases when the #MME# receives a Handover Notifiy message from the eNodeB. The counter is measured on the #MME#.

This measurement provides the number of attempted intra-SGSN/MME IRAT handover procedures from #LTE# access to #UMTS# access. The counter increases when the #MME# receives a Handover Required message with RNC Target ID. The counter is measured on the #MME#.

This measurement provides the number of attempted #IRAT# #PS# Handover procedures from #UMTS# to #LTE#. The counter is incremented when the Forward Relocation Request message arrives at the target #MME# from the source #SGSN# .

This measurement provides the number of attempted #IRAT# #PS# Handover procedures from #LTE# to #UMTS#. The counter is incremented when the Handover Required message arrives at the source #MME# with the Handover Type #IE# set to "LTEtoUTRAN".
This measurement provides the number of successful #IRAT# #PS# Handover procedures from #UMTS# to #LTE#. The counter is incremented when the Handover Notify message arrives at the target #MME#.

This measurement provides the number of successful #IRAT# #PS# Handover procedures from #LTE# to #UMTS#. The counter is incremented when the Forward Relocation Complete Notification message arrives at the source #MME# from the target #SGSN#.

PmGroup.description: This PmGroup defines measurement types within the Mobility_IRATHO_G area.

MeasurementType.description: Counts the number of Inter #IRAT# #PS# Handover attempts in new #SGSN# when moving from #WCDMA# to #GSM#, including possible retransmissions. Trigger: Reception of Forward Relocation Request #GTP-C# message in #GSM# from source#SGSN# when source CELL is #WCDMA#.

Counts the number of Inter #IRAT# #PS# Handover attempts in old #SGSN# #GSM#, including possible retransmissions. Trigger: Reception of #PS# Handover Required #BSSGP# message from #BSS# when Target CELL is situated under cooperating #WCDMA#-#SGSN#.

Counts the number of Intra #SGSN# #IRAT# #PS# Handover from #GSM# to #WCDMA# attempts, including possible retransmissions. Trigger:Reception of #PS# Handover Required #BSSGP# message from #BSS# when Target CELL is situated under own #SGSN# but under #WCDMA# control.
Counts the number of successful Inter #IRAT# #PS# Handovers when moving from #WCDMA# to #GSM#. Trigger: Sending of Forward Relocation Complete #GTP-C# message in #GSM# to source#SGSN# #WCDMA#

Counts the number of successful Inter #IRAT# #PS# Handovers when moving from #GSM# to #WCDMA#. Trigger: Reception of Forward Relocation Complete #GTP-C# message from target#SGSN# #WCDMA# when source#SGSN# is #GSM#.

Counts the number of successful Intra #IRAT# #PS# Handovers when moving from #WCDMA# to #GSM#. Trigger: Reception of #PS# Handover Complete #BSSGP# message from #BSS# when Source CELL is situated under own #SGSN# but under #WCDMA# control.

PmGroup.description: This PmGroup defines measurement types within the Mobility_IRATHO_U area.

MeasurementType.description: Counts the number of Inter #IRAT# #PS# Handover attempts in new #SGSN# #WCDMA#, including possible retransmissions. Trigger: Reception of Forward Relocation Request #GTP-C# message in #WCDMA# from source#SGSN# when source CELL is #GSM#.

Counts the number of Inter #IRAT# #PS# Handover attempts in old #SGSN# when moving from #WCDMA# to #GSM#, including possible retransmissions. Trigger: Reception of Relocation Required #RANAP# message from #RNC# when Target CELL is situated under cooperating #GSM#-#SGSN#.

Counts the number of Intra #IRAT# #PS# Handover attempts when moving from #WCDMA# to #GSM#, including possible retransmissions. Trigger: Reception of Relocation Required #RANAP# message from #RNC# when Target CELL is situated under own #SGSN# but under #GSM# control.

Counts the number of successful Inter #IRAT# #PS# Handovers in new SGSN when moving from #GSM# to #WCDMA#. Trigger: Sending of Forward Relocation Complete #GTP-C# message in #WCDMA# to source#SGSN# #GSM#.

Counts the number of successful Inter #IRAT# #PS# Handovers in old #SGSN# when moving from #WCDMA# to #GSM#. Trigger: Reception of Forward Relocation Complete #GTP-C# message from target#SGSN# #GSM# when source#SGSN# is #WCDMA#.

Counts the number of successful Intra #IRAT# #PS# Handovers when moving from #GSM# to #WCDMA#. Trigger: Reception of Relocation Complete #RANAP# message from #RNC# when Source CELL is situated under own #SGSN# but under #GSM# control.

This measurement provides the number of successful intra-SGSN/MME #IRAT# #PS# handover procedures from #LTE# access to #UMTS# access. The counter increases when the #SGSN# receives a Relocation Complete message from the #RNC#. The counter is measured on the #SGSN#.

This measurement provides the number of incoming inter-SGSN/MME IRAT PS handover requests from #LTE# access to #UMTS# access. The counter increases when the #SGSN# receives a Forward Relocation Request message from the #MME#. The counter is measured on the #SGSN#.

This measurement provides the number of attempted inter-SGSN/MME #IRAT# #PS# handover procedures from #UMTS# access to #LTE# access. The counter increases when the #SGSN# receives a Relocation Required message with eNodeB target ID from the #RNC#. The counter is measured on the #SGSN#.

This measurement provides the number of successful incoming inter-SGSN/MME #IRAT# #PS# handover procedures from #LTE# access to #UMTS# access. The counter increases when the #SGSN# receives a Relocation Complete message from the #RNC#. The counter is measured on the #SGSN#.

This measurement provides the number of successful inter-SGSN/MME #IRAT# #PS# handover procedures from #UMTS# access to #LTE# access. The counter increases when the #SGSN# receives a Forward Relocation Complete Notification message from the #MME#. The counter is measured on the #SGSN#.

This measurement provides the number of attempted intra-SGSN/MME #IRAT# #PS# handover procedures from #UMTS# access to #LTE# access. The counter increases when the #SGSN# receives a Relocation Required message with eNodeB target ID from the #RNC#. The counter is measured on the #SGSN#.

PmGroup.description: This PmGroup defines measurement types within the Mobility_ISYSC area.

MeasurementType.description: This measurement provides the number of intra-SGSN inter-system change procedures being rejected due to the coordination of #CS# and #PS# in a MOCN constellation.
This measurement provides the number of Intra-SGSN ISC procedures being rejected due to the coordination of CS and PS in a MOCN constellation.

The number of Inter-SGSN Inter-System Change RAU messages discarded by the SGSN due to UE Signaling Control. The counter applies only when UE Signaling Control is activated in the Measurement and Control mode. The counter is increased whenever an Inter-SGSN RAU message is identified and discarded during a control period.

The number of Inter-SGSN Inter-System Change RAU messages discarded by the SGSN due to UE Signaling Control. The counter applies only when UE Signaling Control is activated in the Measurement and Control mode. The counter is increased whenever an Inter-SGSN RAU message is identified and discarded during a control period.

This measurement provides the amount of Routing Area Update Request messages of Inter-SGSN RAU Inter-System Change that are controlled by the UE Signaling Control feature with the reject action. The counter applies only when the UE Signaling Control feature is activated in the Measurement and Control mode. The counter is increased whenever a Routing Area Update Request message of Inter-SGSN RAU Inter-System Change is identified and controlled by UE Signaling Control with the reject action during a control period.

PmGroup.description: This PmGroup defines measurement types within the Mobility_ISYSC_E area.

MeasurementType.description: This measurement provides the amount of TAU Request messages of Inter SGSN-MME Inter-System Change TAU with emergency indication that are controlled by the UE Signaling Control feature with the ignore action. The counter applies only when the UE Signaling Control feature is activated in the Measurement and Control mode. The counter is increased whenever a TAU Request message of Inter SGSN-MME Inter-System Change TAU with emergency indication is identified and controlled by UE Signaling Control with the ignore action during a control period.

This measurement provides the amount of TAU Request messages of Intra SGSN-MME Inter-System Change TAU with emergency indication that are controlled by the UE Signaling Control feature with the ignore action. The counter applies only when the UE Signaling Control feature is activated in the Measurement and Control mode. The counter is increased whenever a TAU Request message of Intra SGSN-MME Inter-System Change TAU with emergency indication is identified and controlled by UE Signaling Control with the ignore action during a control period.

This measurement provides the amount of TAU Request messages of Inter SGSN-MME Inter-System Change TAU that are controlled by the UE Signaling Control feature with the ignore action. The counter applies only when the UE Signaling Control feature is activated in the Measurement and Control mode. The counter is increased whenever a TAU Request message of Inter SGSN-MME Inter-System Change TAU is identified and controlled by UE Signaling Control with the ignore action during a control period.

This measurement provides the amount of TAU Request messages of Inter SGSN-MME Inter-System Change TAU that are controlled by the UE Signaling Control feature with the reject action. The counter applies only when the UE Signaling Control feature is activated in the Measurement and Control mode. The counter is increased whenever a TAU Request message of Inter SGSN-MME Inter-System Change TAU is identified and controlled by UE Signaling Control with the reject action during a control period.

This measurement provides the amount of TAU Request messages of Intra SGSN-MME Inter-System Change TAU that are controlled by the UE Signaling Control feature with the ignore action. The counter applies only when the UE Signaling Control feature is activated in the Measurement and Control mode. The counter is increased whenever a TAU Request message of Intra SGSN-MME Inter-System Change TAU is identified and controlled by UE Signaling Control with the ignore action during a control period.

This measurement provides the amount of TAU Request messages of Intra SGSN-MME Inter-System Change TAU that are controlled by the UE Signaling Control feature with the reject action. The counter applies only when the UE Signaling Control feature is activated in the Measurement and Control mode. The counter is increased whenever a TAU Request message of Intra SGSN-MME Inter-System Change TAU is identified and controlled by UE Signaling Control with the reject action during a control period.
This measurement provides the number of attempted #TAU# from both #GnSGSN# and from #S4-SGSN# procedures. Both sent and resent messages from #UE# are counted.
This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful inter-node #ISC# #TAU# procedures (with #RAT# change) that have failed with cause code #11, "Roaming not allowed in this tracking area".
This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful inter-node #ISC# #TAU# procedures (with #RAT# change) that have failed with cause code #12, "Tracking area not allowed".
This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful inter-node #ISC# #TAU# procedures (with #RAT# change) that have failed with cause code #13, "Roaming not allowed in this tracking area".
This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful inter-node #ISC# #TAU# procedures (with #RAT# change) that have failed with cause code #14, "EPS services not allowed in this PLMN".
This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful inter-node #ISC# #TAU# procedures (with #RAT# change) that have failed with cause code #15, "No suitable cells in tracking area".
This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful inter-node #ISC# #TAU# procedures (with #RAT# change) that have failed with cause code #9, "UE identity cannot be derived by the network".

This measurement provides the number of failed inter-node #ISC# #TAU# procedures from #SGSN-MME# procedures (with #RAT# change). Failed TAU, both from #Gn-SGSN# and from #S4-SGSN#, are counted. Both sent and resent messages from the #UE# are counted. This will count inter-node #ISC# #TAU# procedures.
This measurement provides the number of failed #TAU# from #Gn-SGSN# and #S4-SGSN# procedures due to the old #SGSN# not sending #PDP# context or #PDN# connections respectively.

This measurement provides the number of attempted inter-node #ISC# #TAU# from #S4-SGSN# procedures (with #RAT# change). Both sent and resent messages from the #UE# are counted. If the MME can not find any #S4-SGSN#s, it is impossible to determine which type of #SGSN# made the attempt. Therefore attempts that fail because the #MME# is unable to find an #SGSN#, are not counted.

This measurement provides the number of successfully performed inter-node #ISC# #TAU# from #S4-SGSN# procedures (with #RAT# change).The counter is incremented when the #TAU# Accept message is transmitted to the #UE#.
This measurement provides the number of successfully performed #TAU# from both #GnSGSN# and #S4-SGSN# procedures.The counter is incremented when the #TAU# Accept message is transmitted to the #UE#.

This measurement provides the number of attempted intra-node #ISC# #TAU# procedures from #SGSN# procedures (with #RAT# change). Both sent and resent messages from the #UE# are counted. This will count intra-node #ISC# #TAU# procedures both from #Gn-SGSN# and from #S4-SGSN#.
This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful intra-node #ISC# #TAU# procedures (with #RAT# change) that have failed with cause code #11, "PLMN not allowed".
This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful intra-node #ISC# #TAU# procedures (with #RAT# change) that have failed with cause code #12, "Tracking area not allowed".
This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful intra-node #ISC# #TAU# procedures (with #RAT# change) that have failed with cause code #13, "Roaming not allowed in this tracking area".
This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful intra-node #ISC# #TAU# procedures (with #RAT# change) that have failed with cause code #14, "EPS services not allowed in this PLMN".
This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful intra-node #ISC# #TAU# procedures (with #RAT# change) that have failed with cause code #15, "No suitable cells in tracking area".

This measurement provides the number of successfully performed intra-node #ISC# #TAU# from #SGSN# procedures (with #RAT# change). The counter is incremented when a #TAU# Accept message is transmitted to the #UE#. This will count successful intra-node #ISC# #TAU# from both #Gn-SGSN# and from #S4-SGSN#.

PmGroup.description: This PmGroup defines measurement types within the Mobility_MM_E area.

MeasurementType.description: This measurement provides the number of attempted #E-UTRAN# attach procedures initiated within the MME's area.
This measurement provides the number of attempted #MME#-initiated #EPS# detach requests, node total. It is incremented each time a detach request is sent from the MME#.
This measurement provides the number of #UE#-initiated #E-UTRAN# detach procedures within this #MME# area.

This measurement provides the total number of paging procedures based on the latest visited eNodeB list. The counter is incremented when a Paging Request message is sent to an eNodeB in the latest visited eNodeB list. That is at the transmission of the first paging message in a paging selection of LatestVisitedENodeBList within a paging profile. Retransmisson of a Paging Request message based on the latest visited eNodeB list is not counted.

The counter is incremented when a Paging Request is sent to the eNodeB a #UE# has just visisted. That is at the transmission of the first paging message in a paging selection of LastVisitedENodeB within a paging profile. Retransmisson of Paging Request based on last visited eNodeB is not counted.

This measurement gives the total number of paging procedure based on last visted #TA#. The counter is incremented when a Paging Request is sent to the last #TA#. That is at the transmission of the first paging message in a paging selection of LastVisitedTA within a paging profile. Retransmisson of Paging Request based on last visited #TA# is not counted.

This measurement provides the total number of attempted #PS# paging procedures initiated at the #MME# over the #S1-MME# interface. The counter is incremented when a #PS# paging procedure is started, that is at the transmission of the first paging message in the procedure. The paging procedure consists of one or more paging messages with the current #S-TMSI#. Optionally, the paging procedure is followed by paging messages with the old #S-TMSI#. A new set of paging messages, triggered by a new Downlink Data Indication from the Serving Gateway is regarded as a new procedure.
This measurement provides the number of attempted S1 Service request procedures in the MME. It is incremented when an S1 Service Request is received from the UE.

This measurement gives the total number of paging procedure based on whole #TAI# list a #UE# has registered. The counter is incremented when a Paging Request is sent to the whole #TAI# list. That is at the transmission of the first paging message in a paging selection of TAIist within a paging profile. Retransmisson of Paging Request based on TAIlist is not counted.
This measurement provides the number of attempted #E-UTRAN# attach procedures initiated within this #MME# area, with emergency indication.
This measurement provides the number of successfully performed #E-UTRAN# attach procedures initiated within this #MME# area, with emergency indication.

This measurement provides the number of Attach Request messages that have been rejected due to the Attach Throttling function. The counter is incremented when an Attach Request message is rejected because the configured maximum rate has been exceeded. The allowed maximum rate is configured with the MMEAttachThrottlingAttachRateLimit parameter.

This measurement provides the amount of Attach Request messages discarded by the MME due to UE Signaling Control. The counter increases if a message is discarded when the UE Signaling Control rule is in measurement and control mode. Messages are discarded if the value of the ThresholdNumber parameter is exceeded within a measurement interval. The ThresholdNumber parameter is configured in the UE Signaling Control rule.

This measurement provides the amount of Attach Request messages that are controlled by the UE Signaling Control feature with the reject action. The counter applies only when the UE Signaling Control feature is activated in the Measurement and Control mode. The counter is increased whenever an Attach Request message is identified and controlled by UE Signaling Control with the reject action during a control period.

This measurement provides the number of attempted #CS# fallback paging procedures due to #MT# call, initiated at the #MME# over the S1-MME interface. The counter is incremented when a #CS# fallback paging procedure is started, that is at the transmission of the first paging message in the procedure. The paging procedure consists of one or more paging messages with the current S-TMSI. A new set of paging messages, triggered by a new #MT# call from an #MSC/VLR# is regarded as a new procedure.

This measurement provides the number of successful paging procedures initiated due to #MT# call, irrespective of the paging being an initial paging request or resending of the paging request. This counter is incremented each time a paging procedure, due to #CS# fallback, is successfully concluded.

This measurement provides the number of attempted #CS# fallback procedures to #WCDMA# or #GSM#, in the #MME#. It is incremented either when an extended service request for a Mobile Originated #MO# call is received from the #UE# or when a paging request for an #MT# call is received from the #MSC/VLR# over the SGs interface.

This measurement provides the number of successful #CS# fallback procedures to #WCDMA# or #GSM#, in the #MME#. It is incremented each time a #CS# fallback procedure is successfully concluded, at the reception of a #UE# context release complete message.

This measurement provides the amount of Attach Request messages with emergency indication discarded by the MME due to UE Signaling Control. The counter increases if a message is discarded when the UE Signaling Control rule is in measurement and control mode. Messages are discarded if the value of the ThresholdNumber parameter is exceeded within a measurement interval. The ThresholdNumber parameter is configured in the UE Signaling Control rule.

This measurement provides the amount of Extended Service Request messages with emergency indication that are controlled by the UE Signaling Control feature with the ignore action. The counter applies only when the UE Signaling Control feature is activated in the Measurement and Control mode. The counter is increased whenever an Extended Service Request message with emergency indication is identified and controlled by UE Signaling Control with the ignore action during a control period.

This measurement provides the amount of inter-MME Tracking Area Update Request messages with emergency indication discarded by the MME due to UE Signaling Control. The counter increases if a message is discarded when the UE Signaling Control rule is in measurement and control mode. Messages are discarded if the value of the ThresholdNumber parameter is exceeded within a measurement interval. The ThresholdNumber parameter is configured in the UE Signaling Control rule.

This measurement provides the amount of intra-MME Tracking Area Update Request messages with emergency indication discarded by the MME due to UE Signaling Control. The counter increases if a message is discarded when the UE Signaling Control rule is in measurement and control mode. Messages are discarded if the value of the ThresholdNumber parameter is exceeded within a measurement interval. The ThresholdNumber parameter is configured in the UE Signaling Control rule.

This measurement provides the amount of Service Request messages with emergency indication discarded by the MME due to UE Signaling Control. The counter increases if a message is discarded when the UE Signaling Control rule is in measurement and control mode. Messages are discarded if the value of the ThresholdNumber parameter is exceeded within a measurement interval. The ThresholdNumber parameter is configured in the UE Signaling Control rule.
This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful #EPS# attach procedures that have failed with cause code #11, "#PLMN# not allowed".
This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful #EPS# attach procedures that have failed with cause code #12, "Tracking area not allowed".
This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful #EPS# attach procedures that have failed with cause code #13, "Roaming not allowed in this tracking area".
This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful #EPS# attach procedures that have failed with a cause code #14, "#EPS# Services not allowed in this #PLMN#".
This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful #EPS# attach procedures that have failed with cause code #15, "No suitable cells in tracking area".
This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful #MM# attach procedures that have failed with a cause code #17, "Network failure".

This measurement provides the number of failed attach procedures per #MME# due to a blocked #ME#. It is incremented when the #MME# returns an Attach Reject message to the #UE# with cause code #6, Illegal #ME#.
This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful EPS attach procedures that have failed with a cause code #7, "EPS Services not allowed".
This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful EPS attach procedures that have failed with a cause code #8, "EPS Services and non EPS Services not allowed".

This measurement provides the amount of Extended Service Request messages that are controlled by the UE Signaling Control feature with the detach action. The counter applies only when the UE Signaling Control feature is activated in the Measurement and Control mode. The counter is increased whenever an Extended Service Request message is identified and controlled by UE Signaling Control with the detach action during a control period.

This measurement provides the amount of Extended Service Request messages that are controlled by the UE Signaling Control feature with the ignore action. The counter applies only when the UE Signaling Control feature is activated in the Measurement and Control mode. The counter is increased whenever an Extended Service Request message is identified and controlled by UE Signaling Control with the ignore action during a control period.

This measurement provides the amount of Extended Service Request messages that are controlled by the UE Signaling Control feature with the reject action. The counter applies only when the UE Signaling Control feature is activated in the Measurement and Control mode. The counter is increased whenever an Extended Service Request message is identified and controlled by UE Signaling Control with the reject action during a control period.

This measurement provides the number of attempted Extended Service Request procedures for 1xCS fallback to 1xRTT in the #MME#. It is incremented when an Extended Service Request is received from the UE.

This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful Extended Service Request procedures for 1xCS fallback to 1xRTT in the #MME#. It is incremented when a Service Reject message is sent in response to an Extended Service Request.

This measurement provides the number of attempted Inter-MME TAU procedures with SGW relocation. The counter is increased whenever the MME receives a Context Response message and the DNS query is successful. It is also increased whenever the new MME receives a TAU Request message after the Inter-MME S1-Based Handover procedure with SGW relocation is performed.

This measurement provides the number of successful Inter-MME TAU procedures with SGW relocation. The counter is increased whenever a normal Inter-MME TAU with SGW Relocation procedure is completed. It is also increased whenever the TAU is performed successfully after the Inter-MME S1-Based Handover procedure with SGW relocation is performed.

This measurement provides the number of attempted Inter-MME TAU procedures without SGW relocation. The counter is increased whenenver the new MME receives a Context Response message and the DNS query is successful. It is also increased whenever the new MME receives a TAU Request message after the Inter-MME S1-Based Handover procedure without SGW relocation is performed.

This measurement provides the number of successful Inter-MME TAU procedures without SGW relocation. The counter is increased whenever a normal Inter-MME TAU procedure without SGW relocation is completed. It is also increased whenever the Inter-MME TAU is performed successfully after the Inter-MME S1-Based Handover procedure without SGW relocation is performed.

This measurement provides the amount of inter-MME Tracking Area Update Request messages discarded by the MME due to UE Signaling Control. The counter increases if a message is discarded when the UE Signaling Control rule is in measurement and control mode. Messages are discarded if the value of the ThresholdNumber parameter is exceeded within a measurement interval. The ThresholdNumber parameter is configured in the UE Signaling Control rule.

This measurement provides the amount of TAU Request messages of Inter-MME TAU that are controlled by the UE Signaling Control feature with the reject action. The counter applies only when the UE Signaling Control feature is activated in the Measurement and Control mode. The counter is increased whenever a TAU Request message of Inter-MME TAU is identified and controlled by UE Signaling Control with the reject action during a control period.

This measurement provides the number of attempted Intra-MME TAU procedures with SGW relocation. The counter is increased whenever the Security Function is completed and the DNS query is successful. It is also increased whenever the MME receives a TAU Request message after the Intra-MME X2-Based or S1-Based Handover procedure with SGW relocation is performed.

This measurement provides the number of successful Intra-MME TAU procedures with SGW relocation.The counter is increased whenever a normal Intra-MME TAU procedure with SGW relocation is completed. It is also increased whenever the Intra-MME TAU is performed successfully after the Intra-MME X2-Based or S1-Based Handover procedure with SGW relocation is performed.

This measurement provides the number of attempted Intra-MME TAU procedures without SGW relocation. The counter is increased whenever the Security Function is completed and the DNS query is successful. It is also increased whenever the MME receives a TAU Request message after the Intra-MME X2-Based or S1-Based Handover procedure without SGW relocation is performed.
