This measurement provides the number of successful Intra-MME TAU procedures without SGW relocation. The counter is increased whenever a normal Intra-MME TAU procedure without SGW relocation is completed. It is also increased whenever the Intra-MME TAU is performed successfully after the Intra-MME X2-Based or S1-Based Handover procedure without SGW relocation is performed.

This measurement provides the amount of TAU Request messages of Intra-MME TAU that are controlled by the UE Signaling Control feature with the detach action. The counter applies only when the UE Signaling Control feature is activated in the Measurement and Control mode. The counter is increased whenever a TAU Request message of Intra-MME TAU is identified and controlled by UE Signaling Control with the detach action during a control period.

This measurement provides the amount of intra-MME Tracking Area Update Request messages discarded by the MME due to UE Signaling Control. The counter increases if a message is discarded when the UE Signaling Control rule is in measurement and control mode. Messages are discarded if the value of the ThresholdNumber parameter is exceeded within a measurement interval. The ThresholdNumber parameter is configured in the UE Signaling Control rule.

This measurement provides the amount of TAU Request messages of Intra-MME TAU that are controlled by the UE Signaling Control feature with the reject action. The counter applies only when the UE Signaling Control feature is activated in the Measurement and Control mode. The counter is increased whenever a TAU Request message of Intra-MME TAU is identified and controlled by UE Signaling Control with the reject action during a control period.
This measurement provides the number of Location Report messages received in the #MME# from the eNodeB.

This measurement provides the number of attempted Location Update procedures towards an #MSC/VLR#, initiated within the #MME#. This counter is incremented each time a Location Update procedure is started towards an #MSC/VLR#.

This measurement provides the number of successful Location Update procedures towards an #MSC/VLR#, initiated within the #MME#. This counter is incremented each time a Location Update procedure is successfully concluded towards an #MSC/VLR#.

This measurement provides the number of currently attached #UE# within this #MME# area for #IMS# Emergency Service only. The gauge will be incremented or decremented when the #UE# enters or leaves the #MME# with only #IMS# Emergency Service, for example, due to Attach, Inter-#MME# mobility, Detach or Implicit Detach. This gauge will also be increased if an attached user with an additional EMC PDN looses its non-emergency PDNs due to, for example, Roaming restrictions, and then ends up with only IMS Emergency Service.

This measurement provides the number of currently unauthenticated attached UEs within this MME area for IMS emergency service only. The gauge will be incremented or decremented when an unauthenticated UE enters or leaves the MME with only IMS Emergency Service, for example, due to Attach, Inter-MME mobility, Detach or Implicit Detach.

This measurement provides the number of currently attached #EPS# subscribers within this #MME# area. The gauge will be incremented or decremented when the #UE# enters or leaves the #MME#, for example, due to Attach, Inter-#MME# #TA# Update, Detach or Implicit Detach.
MeasurementType.alarmRaiseDefaultLevel: value of 90% of the SAU capacity license limit
MeasurementType.alarmClearDefaultLevel: value of 85% of the SAU capacity license limit

MeasurementType.description: This measurement provides the current number of SGs associated subscribers within this #MME#. The gauge is incremented at each successful initial registration for a #UE# towards an #MSC/VLR#. The gauge is decremented each time a #UE# is #IMSI# detached.
This measurement provides the number of currently disconnected eNodeBs.
This measurement provides the number of subscribers in the ECM-CONNECTED state.

This measurement provides the number of #EPS# home subscribers located in the MME location register. The #EMM# state of this subscriber is EMM_REGISTERED or EMM_DEREGISTERED. Only #EPS# subscribers that are homed in the same #EPS# network are considered.

This measurement provides the number of visiting foreign #EPS# subscribers located in the #MME# location register. The #EMM# state of the subscriber is EMM_REGISTERED or EMM_DEREGISTERED. Only #EPS# subscribers that are homed in an #EPS# network of a foreign country are considered.

This measurement provides the number of visiting national #EPS# subscribers located in the #MME# location register. The #EMM# state of the subscriber is EMM_REGISTERED or EMM_DEREGISTERED. Only #EPS# subscribers that are homed in a partner #EPS# network of the same country are considered.
This measurement provides the number of failed paging procedures with expired quarantine timer. The counter is incremented when the quarantine timer expires before receiving any Initial UE Message.
This measurement provides the number of failed paging procedures that start a quarantine timer for paging.
This measurement provides the number of failed paging procedures that start a quarantine timer for the first time in a quarantine sequence.
This measurement provides the number of S1 releases in the #MME#. Both eNodeB and MME initiated releases are counted. Trigger: Sending UE Context Release Command to the #eNodeB#.

This measurement provides the number of eNodeB-initiated S1 releases due to cause "Radio Connection With UE Lost". Trigger: Sending UE Context Release Command to the #eNodeB#, after receiving a UE Context Release Request or Handover Cancel from the eNodeB with cause "Radio Connection With UE Lost".

This measurement provides the number of eNodeB-initiated S1 releases due to cause "User Inactivity". Trigger: Sending UE Context Release Command to the #eNodeB#, after receiving a UE Context Release Request from the eNodeB with cause "User Inactivity".

This measurement provides the amount of Service Request messages that are controlled by the UE Signaling Control feature with the detach action. The counter applies only when the UE Signaling Control feature is activated in the Measurement and Control mode. The counter is increased whenever a Service Request message is identified and controlled by UE Signaling Control with the detach action during a control period.

This measurement provides the amount of Service Request messages discarded by the MME due to UE Signaling Control. The counter increases if a message is discarded when the UE Signaling Control rule is in measurement and control mode. Messages are discarded if the value of the ThresholdNumber parameter is exceeded within a measurement interval. The ThresholdNumber parameter is configured in the UE Signaling Control rule.

This measurement provides the amount of Service Request messages that are controlled by the UE Signaling Control feature with the reject action. The counter applies only when the UE Signaling Control feature is activated in the Measurement and Control mode. The counter is increased whenever a Service Request message is identified and controlled by UE Signaling Control with the reject action during a control period.

This measurement provides the number of attempted #MT# #SMS# paging procedures due to #MT# #SMS#, initiated at the #MME# over the S1-MME interface. The counter is incremented when an #SMS# paging procedure is started, that is at the transmission of the first paging message in the procedure. The paging procedure consists of one or more paging messages with the current #S-TMSI#. A new set of paging messages, triggered by a new #MT# #SMS# from an #MSC/VLR# is regarded as a new procedure.

This measurement provides the number of successful paging procedures initiated due to #MT# #SMS#, irrespective of the paging being an initial paging request or resending of the paging request. This counter is incremented each time a paging procedure, due to #SMS#, is successfully concluded.

This measurement provides the number of attempted SRVCC CS and PS procedures from LTE to WCDMA. It is incremented when a Handover Required message with the SRVCC HO Indication IE indicating "CS and PS" is received from the eNodeB.

This measurement provides the number of SRVCC CS and PS procedures from LTE to WCDMA where the CS part is successful but the PS part fails. This counter is incremented when a PS to CS Complete Notification is received from MSC and a Forward Relocation Response or Forward Relocation Complete Notification either times out or is received with cause code indicating failure reported by the SGSN.

This measurement provides the number of successful SRVCC CS and PS procedures from LTE to WCDMA. It is incremented when both an SRVCC PS to CS Complete Notification message from the MSC and a Forward Relocation Complete Notification from the SGSN is received.

This measurement provides the number of attempted SRVCC CS Only procedures to GSM in the MME. It is incremented when a Handover Required message with the SRVCC HO Indication IE indicating "CS only" is received from the eNodeB over the S1-MME interface.

This measurement provides the number of successful SRVCC CS only procedures to GSM in the MME. It is incremented each time an SRVCC CS only procedure is successfully concluded, at the reception of an SRVCC PS to CS Complete Notification message from the MSC server over the Sv interface.

This measurement provides the number of attempted SRVCC CS Only procedures to WCDMA in the MME. It is incremented when a Handover Required message with the SRVCC HO Indication IE indicating 'CS only' is received from the eNodeB over the S1-MME interface.

This measurement provides the number of successful SRVCC CS only procedures to WCDMA in the MME. It is incremented each time an SRVCC CS only procedure is successfully concluded, at the reception of an SRVCC PS to CS Complete Notification message from the MSC server over the Sv interface.
This measurement provides the number of successfully performed #E-UTRAN# attach procedures initiated within this #MME# area.
This measurement provides the number of successful #MME#-initiated #EPS# detach requests, node total. It is incremented when the #MME# receives an expected detach accept.

This measurement provides the total number of successful paging procedures based on the latest visited eNodeB list, irrespective of the paging being an initial paging request or the resending of a paging request. The counter is incremented when a Service Request message or any other NAS message from #UE# is received.

This measurement provides the total number of #PS# paging procedures that are successful at the first paging message in the paging procedure. The counter is incremented when a Service Request or any NAS message from UE is received.

This measurement provides the total number of successful paging procedures based on LastVisitedENodeB, irrespective of the paging being an initial paging request or the resending of paging request. The counter is incremented when a Service Request or any NAS message from UE is received.

This measurement provides the total number of successful paging procedures based on LastVisistedTa, irrespective of the paging being an initial paging request or the resending of paging request. The counter is incremented when a Service Request or any NAS message from UE is received.

This measurement provides the total number of successful #PS# paging procedures, irrespective of the paging being an initial paging request or the resending of paging request. The counter is incremented when a Service Request or any NAS message from UE is received.

This measurement provides the total number of successful paging procedures based on TaList, irrespective of the paging being an initial paging request or the resending of paging request. The counter is incremented when a Service Request or any NAS message from UE is received.

This measurement provides a tool monitoring issues in the communication between SGSN-MME and MSC over the SGs interface. This counter is incremented for the following cases:; * SGSN-MME needs to send an SGsAP-LOCATION-UPDATE-REQUEST message to the MSC but cannot due to missing TA-LA mapping configuration.; * SGSN-MME needs to send an SGsAP-LOCATION-UPDATE-REQUEST message to the MSC but cannot due to no LAI can be selected although there are mapped LAIs to the TAI.; * SGSN-MME does not receive a response from the MSC to a SGsAP-LOCATION-UPDATE-REQUEST message.; * SGSN-MME receives an SGsAP-LOCATION-UPDATE-REJECT with any cause code from the MSC.; Action to be taken if the measurement exceeds its supervised threshold: Check the EBM log, and look for L_ATTACH or L_TAU events containing a Sub-Cause Code. Continue with the action proposed for the Sub-Cause Code. The Sub-Cause Code reveals if the problem is missing TA-LA mapping configuration, or no mapped LA can be used due to being restricted by access restriction or LA selection profile, or missing response from the MSC, or reject from the MSC (including the cause code given by the MSC). The EBM log also reveals which TA(s), LA(s), and MSC(s) the problem is related to. It may happen that this counter is incremented but nothing is visible in the EBM log. This happens in case MSC pool is deployed and Location Update fails towards the MSC initially selected but succeeds after fallback to another MSC in the pool. In this case capture the SGs traffic with ITC and search for SGsAP-LOCATION-UPDATE-REJECT or no response to SGsAP-LOCATION-UPDATE-REQUEST.
This measurement provides the number of attempted Inter-#MME# #TAU# procedures initiated within this #MME# area. Both sent and resent messages from UEs are counted.
This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful inter-MME #TAU# procedures that have failed with cause code #11, "PLMN not allowed".
This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful inter-MME #TAU# procedures that have failed with cause code #12, "Tracking area not allowed".
This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful inter-MME #TAU# procedures that have failed with cause code #13, "Roaming not allowed in this tracking area".
This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful inter-MME #TAU# procedures that have failed with a cause code #14, "EPS services not allowed in this PLMN".
This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful inter-MME #TAU# procedures that have failed with cause code #15, "No suitable cells in tracking area".

This measurement provides the number of failed Inter-MME TAU procedures over the S10 interface due to cause code 6. The counter is increased whenever the MME receives a TAU Reject message with cause code 6 (Illegal ME).

This measurement provides the number of failed Inter-MME TAU procedures over the S10 interface due to cause code 8. The counter is increased whenever the MME receives a TAU Reject messsage with cause code 8 (Not authorized EPS and non-EPS service).
This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful Inter-#MME# #TAU# procedures initiated in this #MME# which resulted in cause code #9, "UE identity cannot be derived by the network".

This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful Inter-#MME# #TAU# procedures initiated in this #MME#. The counter is incremented when the Tracking Area Update Reject message is transmitted to the #UE#. #Note: The number of succesful attempts substracted from the total number of attempts does not equal the number of unsuccessful procedures due to discarded and resent messages. Note#

This measurement provides the number of successfully performed Inter-#MME# #TAU# procedures initiated in this #MME#. The counter is incremented when the Tracking Area Update Accept message is transmitted to the #UE#.

This measurement provides the number of attempted Intra-#MME# #TAU# procedures initiated within this #MME# area. Both sent and resent messages from UEs are counted. All types of intra-MME #TAU# requests are counted, that is, both Intra-MME #TAU# and Periodic #TAU#.
This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful intra-#MME#, intra-#RAT# #TAU# procedures that have failed with cause code #11, "PLMN not allowed".
This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful intra-#MME#, intra-#RAT# #TAU# procedures that have failed with cause code #12, "Tracking area not allowed".
This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful intra-#MME#, intra-#RAT# #TAU# procedures that have failed with cause code #13, "Roaming not allowed in this tracking area".
This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful intra-#MME#, intra-#RAT# #TAU# procedures that have failed with cause code #14, "EPS services not allowed in tracking area".
This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful intra-#MME#, intra-#RAT# #TAU# procedures that have failed with cause code #15, "No suitable cells in tracking area".
This measurement provides the number of successfully performed Periodic and Intra-#MME# #TAU# procedures initiated in this #MME#.
This measurement provides the number of attempted Periodic TAU procedures initiated within this MME area. Both sent and resent messages from UEs are counted.
This measurement provides the number of successfully performed Periodic TAU procedures initiated within this MME area.

This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful #E-UTRAN# attach requests per MME This counter is increased whenever an Attach Reject message is sent except for being sent by the reject action of UE Signaling Control. Note: The number of successful attempts subtracted from the total number of attempts does not equal the number of unsuccessful attempts due to discarded messages, resent messages, and messages controlled by the UE Signaling Control feature.

This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful #EPS# attach procedures per #MME# due to cause code 27 (Unknown or missing APN), and cause code 28 (Unknown PDN address or PDN type). The counter is incremented when the #MME# receives corresponding failure causes from the #S-GW#.

This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful #EPS# attach procedures per #MME# due to cause code 32 (Service option not supported), and cause code 33 (Requested Service Option not subscribed). The counter is incremented if the #PDN# Type is not supported or if the request is denied in the #MME# due to subscriber data restriction.

This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful S1 Service Request procedures in the MME. This counter is increased whenever an Service Reject message is sent except for being sent by the reject action of UE Signaling Control.

This measurement provides the number of failed Update Location Answer procedures over the S6a interface with cause code 5001. The counter is increased whenever the MME receives an Update Location Answer message with cause code 5001 (User unknown).

This measurement provides the number of failed Update Location procedures over the S6a interface with cause code 5004. The counter is increased whenever the MME receives an Update Location Answer message with cause code 5004 (Roaming not allowed).

This measurement provides the number of failed Update Location procedures over the S6a interface with cause code 5420. The counter is increased whenever the MME receives an Update Location Answer message with cause code 5420 (Unkown EPS subscription).

This measurement provides the number of failed Update Location procedures over the S6a interface with cause code 5421. The counter is increased whenever the MME receives an Update Location Answer message with cause code 5421 (RAT not allowed).

PmGroup.description: This PmGroup defines measurement types within the Mobility_MM_G area.

MeasurementType.description: This is the name of the counter that gives the number of 'Attach Accept' messages that are altered during retransmission due to non 3GPP compliant #UEs#. The parameter is only valid for #GSM#.

This is the name of the counter that gives the number of 'Authentication and Ciphering Request' messages that are altered during retransmission due to non #3GPP# compliant #UEs#. The parameter is only valid for #GSM#.

This measurement provides the number of attempted GPRS detaches initiated by the HLR within an SGSN. It is incremented when a Cancel Location message is received from the HLR with the cancellation type "subscription withdrawn". Resent Cancel Location messages from the HLR are also counted.
Incremented when #SGSN# detects a change in offset and/or daylight savings time in #SGSNs# handling of #MS# local time.
This measurement provides the number of attempted detach of inactive subscribers procedures within this #SGSN# area.

This measurement provides the amount of Intra-SGSN Routing Area Update messages that are discarded by UE Signaling Control. Incremented when UE Signaling Control is activated, and when it identifies a Intra-SGSN Routing Area Request message from a UE during a control period. Applies to GSM systems only.

This is the name of the counter that gives the number of 'Routing Area Update Accept' messages that are altered during retransmission due to non #3GPP# compliant #UEs#. The parameter is only valid for #GSM#.

This measurement provides the number of attached subscribers within this #SGSN-MME# area. Note that this gauge reflects the correct number of attached subscribers in the #SGSN-MME#. The gauge will then be incremented and decremented in other cases as well, that is, Inter-#SGSN# #RA# Update, Implicitly Detached, and so on. Note: The triggering and clearing levels needs to be changed manually or by triggering a manual small restart when the #SAU# capacity license value is changed. Action to be taken if the measurement exceeds its supervised threshold: This is an indication that the #SGSN-MME# is approaching the maximum number of attached subscribers. Offload the #SGSN-MME#, for example, by moving one or more #BSC#s to a less loaded #SGSN-MME#.
MeasurementType.alarmRaiseDefaultLevel: value of 90% of the SAU capacity license limit
MeasurementType.alarmClearDefaultLevel: value of 85% of the SAU capacity license limit

MeasurementType.description: This measurement provides the number of attached subscriber within this #SGSN# area with #CAMEL# service. The counter is not incremented if the subscriber only have O-SMS CAMEL activated, and not GPRS CAMEL. Note: The triggering and clearing levels needs to be changed manually or by triggering a manual small restart when the #SAU# capacity license value is changed.
MeasurementType.alarmRaiseDefaultLevel: value of 40% of the SAU capacity license limit
MeasurementType.alarmClearDefaultLevel: value of 35% of the SAU capacity license limit

MeasurementType.description: This measurement provides the number of #GPRS# home subscribers located in the #SGSN# location register. The #GPRS# #MM# state of this subscriber is GMM_REGISTERED or GMM_DEREGISTERED. Only #GPRS# subscribers that are homed in the same #GPRS# network are considered.

This measurement provides the number of registered subscribers in the #SGSN# where these subscribers are configured as home subscribers, but the #MCC# in the #RAI# of the #RA# these subscribers access is different from the #MCC# in their #IMSI# numbers. The #GPRS# #MM# state of these subscribers is GMM_REGISTERED or MM_DEREGISTERED. Only #GPRS# subscribers that are homed in a #GPRS# network of a foreign country are considered.

This measurement provides the number of registered subscribers in the #SGSN# where these subscribers are configured as home subscribers, but the #MNC# in the #RAI# of the #RA# these subscribers access is different from the #MNC# in their #IMSI# numbers. The #GPRS# #MM# state of these subscribers is GMM_REGISTERED or MM_DEREGISTERED. Only #GPRS# subscribers that are homed in a partner #GPRS# network of the same country are considered.
This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful #MM# attach procedures which returns cause code #11, "PLMN not allowed".
This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful #MM# attach procedures which returns cause code #13, "Roaming not allowed in this location area".
This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful #MM# attach procedures which returns cause code #14, "GPRS services not allowed in this PLMN".
This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful #MM# attach procedures, which returns cause code #15, "No suitable cells in location area".
This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful #MM# attach procedures, which returns cause code #17, "Network failure".
This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful Attach procedures with the cause code #17 "Network Failure" and the SGSN provides Redirection Indication to the BSC in a MOCN constellation.
This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful #MM# attach procedures which returns cause code #22, "Congestion".

This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful MM attach procedures per SGSN due to cause code #6, "Illegal ME". It is incremented when the SGSN returns an Attach Reject message to the MS with cause code #6 or aborts the attach procedure due to an IMEISV check failure without sending the reject message.
This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful #MM# attach procedures which returns cause code #7, "GPRS Services not allowed".
This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful #MM# attach procedures which returns cause code #8, "GPRS and non GPRS services not allowed".
This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful MM attach procedures which returns cause code #96, "Mandatory information element error".
This measurement provides the number of Attach procedures being rejected due to the coordination of CS and PS in a MOCN constellation.
This measurement provides the number of Inter SGSN RAU procedures being rejected due to the coordination of CS and PS in a MOCN constellation.

This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful #MM# inter-#RAU# procedures, that is, whenever a Routing Area Update Reject message is sent to the #MS#. Action to be taken if the measurement exceeds its supervised threshold: This is an indication of high inter routing area failure rates, typically caused by roaming agreements. To find out if there are real problems, subtract the unsuccessful inter routing area requests due to cause code 9 (MS identity cannot be derived by the network), cause code 14 (#GPRS# services not allowed in this #PLMN#) and cause code 15 (No Suitable Cells In Location Area).
This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful #MM# inter-#RAU# procedures, that is, whenever a Routing Area Update Reject message is sent to the #MS# with cause code #10, Implicitly detached.
This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful #MM# inter-#RA# Update procedures, which returns cause code #14, "GPRS services not allowed in this PLMN".

This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful #MM# inter-#RAU# procedures, that is, whenever a Routing Area Update Reject message is sent to the MS with cause code #15, No Suitable Cells In Location Area.
This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful #MM# inter-#RA# Update procedures, which returns cause code #17, "Network failure".
This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful #MM# inter-#RA# Update procedures, which returns cause code #9, "MS identity cannot be derived by the network".

This measurement provides the number of Intra-SGSN RAU procedures being rejected due to the coordination of CS and PS in a MOCN constellation. The Intra-SGSN ISC procedures are not included in this measurement.

This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful #MM# intra-SGSN #RAU# procedures, that is, whenever a Routing Area Update Reject message is sent to the #MS#. The intra-SGSN #ISC# procedures are not included in this measurement. Action to be taken if the measurement exceeds its supervised threshold: This is an indication of high intra routing area failure rates, typically caused by roaming agreements. To find out if there are real problems, subtract the unsuccessful intra routing area updates due to cause code 14 (#GPRS# services not allowed in this #PLMN#) and cause code 15 (No Suitable Cells In Location Area).

This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful #MM# intra-SGSN #RA# update procedures that return cause code #14, "GPRS services not allowed in this PLMN". The intra-SGSN #ISC# procedures are not included in this measurement.

This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful #MM# intra-SGSN #RA# update procedures that return cause code #15, "No Suitable Cells In Location Area". The intra-SGSN #ISC# procedures are not included in this measurement.

This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful #MM# intra-SGSN #RA# update procedures that return cause code #17, "Network failure". The intra-SGSN #ISC# procedures are not included in this measurement.

This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful RAU procedures with the cause code #17 "Network Failure" and the SGSN provides Redirection Indication to the BSC in a MOCN constellation. Intra-RAU, inter-RAU and ISC are all counted.
This measurement provides the number of detached inactive subscribers within this #SGSN# area.

This measurement provides the total number of attempted paging procedures based on last visited cell. This counter is incremented when a Paging Request message is sent to the cell the UE has just visited. That is at the transmission of the first paging message in a paging selection of LastVisitedCell within a paging profile. Retransmisson of Paging Request messages based on last visited cell is not counted.

This measurement provides the total number of paging procedure based on the RA a UE has registered. The counter is incremented when a Paging Request is sent to the whole RA. That is at the transmission of the first paging message in a paging selection of RA within a paging profile. Retransmisson of Paging Request based on RA is not counted.

The number of Attach Request messages discarded by the SGSN due to UE Signaling Control. The counter applies only when UE Signaling Control is activated in the Measurement and Control mode. The counter is increased whenever an Attach Request message is identified and discarded during a control period.

The number of Inter-SGSN RAU messages discarded by the SGSN due to UE Signaling Control. The counter applies only when UE Signaling Control is activated in the Measurement and Control mode. The counter is increased whenever an Inter-SGSN RAU message is identified and discarded during a control period.

This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful RAU procedures due to no IPv4 address in GGSN/PGW control plane or user plane in the (SGSN) Context Response in WCDMA access. Action to be taken if the measurement exceeds its supervised threshold: To find out the problems, check the MME/SGSN from which the UE comes. The UE may activate PDP context/EPS bearer with only IPv6 address in the GGSN/PGW control plane or user plane.

This measurement provides the total number of successful paging procedures based on LastVisitedCell, irrespective of the paging being an initial Paging Request message or the resending of a Paging Request message. The counter is incremented when an LLC Frame from MS is received.

This measurement provides the total number of successful paging procedures based on RA, irrespective of the paging being an initial paging request or the resending of paging request. The counter is incremented when an LLC Frame from MS is received.

PmGroup.description: This PmGroup defines measurement types within the Mobility_MM_G_RA area.

MeasurementType.description: This measurement provides the number of combined #RA#/#LA# updates (inter-#SGSN#) procedures initiated in this #SGSN#. These are counted as attempts.

This measurement provides the number of combined #RA#/#LA# updates (intra-SGSN) procedures initiated in this #SGSN#. These are counted as attempts. The intra-SGSN #ISC# procedures are not included in this measurement.
This measurement provides the number of attempted #GPRS# attach procedures initiated within this #SGSN# area.
This measurement provides the number of #MS#-initiated #GPRS# detach procedures within this #SGSN# area.
This measurement provides the number of attempted #GPRS# detach procedures initiated by #SGSN#.
This measurement provides the number of combined #RA#/#LA# updates with #IMSI# attach (inter-#SGSN#) procedures initiated in this #SGSN#. These are counted as attempts.

This measurement provides the number of combined #RA#/#LA# updates with #IMSI# attach (intra-SGSN) procedures initiated in this #SGSN#. These are counted as attempts. The intra-SGSN #ISC# procedures are not included in this measurement.
This measurement provides the number of attempted inter-#SGSN# #RA# Update procedures initiated in this #SGSN#.
This measurement provides the number of attempted intra-SGSN #RA# update procedures initiated within this #SGSN# area. The intra-SGSN #ISC# procedures are not included in this measurement.

This measurement provides the number of attempted normal intra-SGSN #RA# update procedures initiated in this #SGSN#. Periodic #RA# updates and #RA# updates acting as resume of a suspended #MS# are not counted. Resending from #MSs# is also counted. The intra-SGSN #ISC# procedures are not included in this measurement.

This measurement provides the number of attempted #PS# paging procedures initiated at the #SGSN# over the Gb interface. The counter is incremented when a #PS# paging procedure is started, that is at the transmission of the first paging message in the procedure. The paging procedure consists of one or more paging messages with the current #P-TMSI#, optionally followed by paging messages with the old #P-TMSI#. A new set of paging messages, triggered by a new #DL# #PDU#, is regarded as a new procedure. Paging with #IMSI# (due to abnormal situation) is also regarded as a new procedure.

This measurement provides the number of attached subscribers per #RA# within this SGSN. Note: The triggering and clearing levels needs to be changed manually or by triggering a manual small restart when the #SAU# capacity license value is changed.
MeasurementType.alarmRaiseDefaultLevel: value of 90% of the SAU capacity license limit
MeasurementType.alarmClearDefaultLevel: value of 85% of the SAU capacity license limit

MeasurementType.description: This measurement provides the number of successfully performed combined #RA#/#LA# updates (inter-#SGSN#) procedures initiated in this #SGSN#.

This measurement provides the number of successfully performed combined #RA#/#LA# update (intra-SGSN) procedures initiated in this #SGSN#. The intra-SGSN #ISC# procedures are not included in this measurement.
This measurement provides the total number of successful PS paging procedures that are successful at the first paging message in the paging procedure.
This measurement provides the number of successfully performed #GPRS# attach procedures within this #SGSN# area.
This measurement provides the number of successfully completed #SGSN#-initiated #GPRS# detach procedures within this #SGSN# area.
This measurement provides the number of successfully completed inter-#SGSN# #RA# Update procedures in this #SGSN#. The counter is incremented when #RAU# Accept is transmitted.
This measurement provides the number of successfully performed intra-SGSN #RA# update procedures initiated in this #SGSN#. The intra-SGSN #ISC# procedures are not included in this measurement.

This measurement provides the number of successfully performed normal intra-SGSN #RA# update procedures initiated in this #SGSN#. Periodic #RA# updates and #RA# updates acting as resume of a suspended #MS# are not counted. The counter is not stepped when resending a #RA# Update Accept message to the #MS#. The intra-SGSN #ISC# procedures are not included in this measurement.

This measurement provides the number of successful #PS# paging procedures initiated at the #SGSN# over the Gb interface. The initial paging procedures as well as the repeated paging procedures are counted.

PmGroup.description: This PmGroup defines measurement types within the Mobility_MM_G_U area.

MeasurementType.description: This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful #MM# attach and inter-#SGSN# #RAU# procedures due to the capacity license SAU Attach Limit being exceeded.

This measurement provides the number of attempted T-ADS requests from HLR. It is incremented when a Provide Subscriber Information message with the Requested Info IE indicating T-ADS is received from HLR.

PmGroup.description: This PmGroup defines measurement types within the Mobility_MM_Hss area.

MeasurementType.description: This measurement provides the number of attempted S6a/S6d Purge UE procedures in the SGSN-MME.
This measurement provides the number of successful S6a/S6d Purge UE procedures in the SGSN-MME.

This measurement provides the number of attempted T-ADS requests from HSS. It is incremented when an Insert Subscriber Data Request message with the IDR-flags IE indicating T-ADS Data Request is received from HSS.
This measurement provides the number of attempted S6a/S6d Update Location procedures in the SGSN-MME.
This measurement provides the number of successful S6a/S6d Update Location procedures in the SGSN-MME.

PmGroup.description: This PmGroup defines measurement types within the Mobility_MM_RA area.

MeasurementType.description: This measurement provides the number of attached subscribers using USIM per RA within an SGSN. It includes the attached USIM users with GSM access and UMTS access. This guage is incremented when a USIM subscriber is attached and decremented when it is detached. For an RA Update, the old RA indexed gauge is decremented and the new RA indexed gauge is incremented.

PmGroup.description: This PmGroup defines measurement types within the Mobility_MM_U area.

MeasurementType.description: This is the name of the counter that gives the number of 'Attach Accept' messages that are altered during retransmission due to non #3GPP# compliant #UEs#. The parameter is only valid for #WCDMA#.

This is the name of the counter that gives the number of 'Authentication and Ciphering Request' messages that are altered during retransmission due to non #3GPP# compliant #UEs#. The parameter is only valid for #WCDMA#.

This measurement provides the number of attempted GPRS detaches initiated by the HLR within an SGSN. It is incremented when a Cancel Location message is received from the HLR with the cancellation type "subscription withdrawn". Resent Cancel Location messages from the HLR are also counted.
Incremented when #SGSN# detects a change in offset and/or daylight savings time in #SGSNs# handling of #MS# local time.
This measurement provides the number of attempted detach of inactive subscribers procedures within this SGSN area.

This measurement provides the amount of Intra-SGSN Routing Area Update messages that are discarded by UE Signaling Control. Incremented when UE Signaling Control is activated, and when it identifies a Intra-SGSN Routing Area Request message from a UE during a control period. Applies to WCDMA systems only.

This is the name of the counter that gives the number of 'Routing Area Update Accept' messages that are altered during retransmission due to non #3GPP# compliant #UEs#. The parameter is only valid for #WCDMA#.
This measurement provides the number of attempted Service request procedures of data type in the #SGSN#. It is incremented when Service request, with service type data, is received from the MS.

This measurement provides the number of attempted Service request procedures of data, signaling, or paging response type, in the #SGSN#. It is incremented when a Service Request is received from the #MS#.

This measurement provides the amount of Service Request messages for data, signaling, and paging response types that are discarded by UE Signaling Control. Incremented when UE Signaling Control is activated, and when it identifies a Service Request message from a UE during a control period.

This measurement provides the number of attached subscribers within this #SGSN-MME# area. Note that this gauge reflects the correct number of attached subscribers in the #SGSN-MME#. The gauge will then be incremented and decremented in other cases as well, that is, Inter-#SGSN# #RA# Update, Implicitly Detached, and so on. Note: The triggering and clearing levels needs to be changed manually or by triggering a manual small restart when the #SAU# capacity license value is changed. Action to be taken if the measurement exceeds its supervised threshold: This is an indication that the #SGSN-MME# is approaching the maximum number of attached subscribers. Offload the #SGSN-MME#, for example, by moving one or more #RNC#s to a less loaded #SGSN-MME#.
MeasurementType.alarmRaiseDefaultLevel: value of 90% of the SAU capacity license limit
MeasurementType.alarmClearDefaultLevel: value of 85% of the SAU capacity license limit

MeasurementType.description: This measurement provides the number of attached subscriber within this #SGSN# area with #CAMEL# service. Note: The triggering and clearing levels needs to be changed manually or by triggering a manual small restart when the #SAU# capacity license value is changed.
MeasurementType.alarmRaiseDefaultLevel: value of 40% of the SAU capacity license limit
MeasurementType.alarmClearDefaultLevel: value of 35% of the SAU capacity license limit

MeasurementType.description: This measurement provides the number of #GPRS# home subscribers located in the #SGSN# location register. The #GPRS# #MM# state of this subscriber is GMM_REGISTERED or GMM_DEREGISTERED. Only #GPRS# subscribers that are homed in the same #GPRS# network are considered.
This measurement provides the number of subscribers in PMM-CONNECTED state.

This measurement provides the number of registered subscribers in the #SGSN# where these subscribers are configured as home subscribers, but the #MCC# in the #RAI# of the #RA# these subscribers access is different from the #MCC# in their #IMSI# numbers. The #GPRS# #MM# state of these subscribers is GMM_REGISTERED or MM_DEREGISTERED. Only #GPRS# subscribers that are homed in a #GPRS# network of a foreign country are considered.

This measurement provides the number of registered subscribers in the #SGSN# where these subscribers are configured as home subscribers, but the #MNC# in the #RAI# of the #RA# these subscribers access is different from the #MNC# in their #IMSI# numbers. The #GPRS# #MM# state of these subscribers is GMM_REGISTERED or MM_DEREGISTERED. Only #GPRS# subscribers that are homed in a partner #GPRS# network of the same country are considered.
This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful #MM# attach procedures which returns cause code #11, "PLMN not allowed".
This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful #MM# attach procedures which returns cause code #13, "Roaming not allowed in this location area".
This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful #MM# attach procedures which returns cause code #14, "GPRS services not allowed in this PLMN".
This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful #MM# attach procedures which returns cause code #15, "No suitable cells in location area".
This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful #MM# attach procedures, which returns cause code #17, "Network failure".
This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful #MM# attach procedures which returns cause code #22, "Congestion".

This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful MM attach procedures per SGSN due to cause code #6, "Illegal ME". It is incremented when the SGSN returns an Attach Reject message to the MS with cause code #6 or aborts the attach procedure due to an IMEISV check failure without sending the reject message.
This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful #MM# attach procedures which returns cause code #7, "GPRS Services not allowed".
This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful #MM# attach procedures which returns cause code #8, "GPRS and non GPRS services not allowed".
This measurement provides the number of attach procedures being rejected due to coordination of #CS# and #PS# in a #MOCN# constellation.
This measurement provides the number of Inter #SGSN# Routing Area Update procedures being rejected due to coordination of #CS# and #PS# in a #MOCN# constellation.

This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful #MM# inter-#RAU# procedures, that is, whenever a Routing Area Update Reject message is sent to the #MS#. This is an indication of high inter routing area failure rates, typically caused by roaming agreements. To find out if there are real problems, subtract the unsuccessful inter routing area requests due to cause code 9 (MS identity cannot be derived by the network), cause code 14 (#GPRS# services not allowed in this #PLMN#) and cause code 15 (No Suitable Cells In Location Area).
This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful #MM# inter-#RAU# procedures, that is, whenever a Routing Area Update Reject message is sent to the #MS# with cause code #10, Implicitly detached.
This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful #MM# inter-#RA# Update procedures, which returns cause code #14, "GPRS services not allowed in this PLMN".

This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful #MM# inter-#RAU# procedures, that is, whenever a Routing Area Update Reject message is sent to the #MS# with cause code #15, No Suitable Cells In Location Area.
This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful #MM# inter-#RA# Update procedures, which returns cause code #17, "Network failure".
This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful #MM# inter-#RA# Update procedures, which returns cause code #9, "MS identity cannot be derived by the network".

This measurement provides the number of intra-SGSN #RAU# procedures being rejected due to the coordination of #CS# and #PS# in a #MOCN# constellation. The intra-SGSN #ISC# procedures are not included in this measurement.

This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful #MM# intra-SGSN #RAU# procedures, that is, whenever a Routing Area Update Reject message is sent to the #MS#. The intra-SGSN #ISC# procedures are not included in this measurement. Action to be taken if the measurement exceeds its supervised threshold: This is an indication of high intra routing area failure rates, typically caused by roaming agreements. To find out if there are real problems, subtract the unsuccessful intra routing area updates due to cause code 14 (#GPRS# services not allowed in this #PLMN#) and cause code 15 (No Suitable Cells In Location Area).

This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful #MM# intra-SGSN #RA# update procedures that return cause code #14, "GPRS services not allowed in this PLMN". The intra-SGSN #ISC# procedures are not included in this measurement.

This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful #MM# intra-SGSN #RA# update procedures that return cause code #15, "No Suitable Cells In Location Area". The intra-SGSN #ISC# procedures are not included in this measurement.

This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful #MM# intra-SGSN #RA# update procedures that return cause code #17, "Network failure". The intra-SGSN #ISC# procedures are not included in this measurement.

This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful Service Request procedures in the #SGSN#. This counter is increased whenever an Service Reject message is sent except for being sent by the reject action of UE Signaling Control.
This measurement provides the number of detached inactive subscribers within this SGSN area.

The number of Attach Request messages discarded by the SGSN due to UE Signaling Control. The counter applies only when UE Signaling Control is activated in the Measurement and Control mode. The counter is increased whenever an Attach Request message is identified and discarded during a control period.

This measurement provides the amount of Attach Request messages that are controlled by the UE Signaling Control feature with the reject action. The counter applies only when the UE Signaling Control feature is activated in the Measurement and Control mode. The counter is increased whenever an Attach Request message is identified and controlled by UE Signaling Control with the reject action during a control period.

This measurement is part of the "HSS/HLR-selection based on EPC Capability" function. It provides the number of attempted fallbacks to #HLR# after a failed #HSS# answer. Trigger: the initiation of a Send Authentication Info-, or a Send Parameters-, or an Update #GPRS# Location-service to the #HLR# after a failed #HSS# answer.

This measurement is part of the "HSS/HLR-selection based on EPC Capability" function. It provides the number of successful transactions to #HLR# after a previous #HSS#/#HLR#-fallback. Trigger: the successful completion of a Send Authentication Info-, or a Send Parameters-, or an Update #GPRS# Location-service to the #HLR# after a failed #HSS# answer.

The number of Inter-SGSN RAU messages discarded by the SGSN due to UE Signaling Control. The counter applies only when UE Signaling Control is activated in the Measurement and Control mode. The counter is increased whenever an Inter-SGSN RAU message is identified and discarded during a control period.

This measurement provides the amount of Routing Area Update Request messages of Inter-SGSN RAU that are controlled by the UE Signaling Control feature with the reject action. The counter applies only when the UE Signaling Control feature is activated in the Measurement and Control mode. The counter is increased whenever a Routing Area Update Request message of Inter-SGSN RAU is identified and controlled by UE Signaling Control with the reject action during a control period.

This measurement provides the amount of Routing Area Update Request messages of Intra-SGSN RAU that are controlled by the UE Signaling Control feature with the detach action. The counter applies only when the UE Signaling Control feature is activated in the Measurement and Control mode. The counter is increased whenever a Routing Area Update Request message of Intra-SGSN RAU is identified and controlled by UE Signaling Control with the detach action during a control period.

This measurement provides the amount of Routing Area Update Request messages of Intra-SGSN RAU that are controlled by the UE Signaling Control feature with the reject action. The counter applies only when the UE Signaling Control feature is activated in the Measurement and Control mode. The counter is increased whenever a Routing Area Update Request message of Intra-SGSN RAU is identified and controlled by UE Signaling Control with the reject action during a control period.
This measurement provides the number of Iu releases in the #SGSN#. Both #RNC# and SGSN initiated releases are counted. Trigger: Sending Iu Release Command to the RNC.

This measurement provides the number of RNC-initiated Iu releases due to cause "Radio Connection With UE Lost". Trigger: Sending Iu Release Command to the RNC after receiving an Iu Release Request with cause "Radio Connection With UE Lost".

This measurement provides the number of RNC-initiated Iu releases due to cause "User Inactivity". Trigger: Sending Iu Release Command to the RNC after receiving an Iu Release Request with cause "User Inactivity".

This measurement provides the number of attached subscribers which are network sharing non-supporting UEs within the MOCN enabled #SGSN-MME# area. Note that this gauge reflects the correct number of attached subscribers which are network sharing non-supporting UEs in the MOCN enabled #SGSN-MME#. The gauge is incremented and decremented in other cases as well, that is, Inter-#SGSN# #RA# Update, Implicitly Detached, and so on.

This measurement provides the number of attached subscribers which are network sharing supporting UEs within the MOCN enabled #SGSN-MME# area. Note that this gauge reflects the correct number of attached subscribers which are network sharing supporting UEs in the MOCN enabled #SGSN-MME#. The gauge is incremented and decremented in other cases as well, that is, Inter-#SGSN# #RA# Update, Implicitly Detached, and so on.

This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful RAU procedures due to no IPv4 address in GGSN/PGW control plane or user plane in the (SGSN) Context Response in WCDMA access. Action to be taken if the measurement exceeds its supervised threshold: To find out the problems, check the MME/SGSN from which the UE comes. The UE may activate PDP context/EPS bearer with only IPv6 address in the GGSN/PGW control plane or user plane.

This measurement provides the amount of Service Request messages that are controlled by the UE Signaling Control feature with the detach action. The counter applies only when the UE Signaling Control feature is activated in the Measurement and Control mode. The counter is increased whenever a Service Request message is identified and controlled by UE Signaling Control with the detach action during a control period.

This measurement provides the amount of Service Request messages that are controlled by the UE Signaling Control feature with the reject action. The counter applies only when the UE Signaling Control feature is activated in the Measurement and Control mode. The counter is increased whenever a Service Request message is identified and controlled by UE Signaling Control with the reject action during a control period.

PmGroup.description: This PmGroup defines measurement types within the Mobility_MM_U_RA area.

MeasurementType.description: This measurement provides the number of attempted #GPRS# attach procedures initiated within this #SGSN# area.
This measurement provides the number of #MS#-initiated #GPRS# detach procedures within this #SGSN# area.
This measurement provides the number of attempted #GPRS# detach procedures initiated by #SGSN#.
This measurement provides the number of attempted inter-#SGSN# #RA# Update procedures initiated in this #SGSN#.
This measurement provides the number of attempted intra-SGSN #RA# update procedures initiated within this #SGSN# area. The intra-SGSN #ISC# procedures are not included in this measurement.

This measurement provides the number of attempted normal intra-SGSN #RA# update procedures initiated in this #SGSN#. Periodic #RA# updates are not counted. Resending from #MSs# is also counted. The intra-SGSN #ISC# procedures are not included in this measurement.

This measurement provides the number of attempted #PS# paging procedures initiated at the #SGSN# over the Iu interface. The counter is incremented when a #PS# paging procedure is started, that is at the transmission of the first paging message in the procedure. The paging procedure consists of one or more paging messages with the current #P-TMSI#, optionally followed by paging messages with the old #P-TMSI#. A new set of paging messages, triggered by a new #DL# #PDU#, is regarded as a new procedure. Paging with #IMSI# (due to abnormal situation) is also regarded as a new procedure.

This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful attach request per #SGSN#. This counter is increased whenever an Attach Reject message is sent except for being sent by the reject action of UE Signaling Control. That is, packet switching paging procedures that are re-started when the previous attempt has timed out. The counter is incremented when a #PS# paging procedure has failed. That is, at timeout after transmission of the last paging message in the procedure. The paging procedure consists of one or more paging messages with the current #P-TMSI#, optionally followed by paging messages with the old #P-TMSI#. A new set of paging messages, triggered by a new #DL# #PDU#, is regarded as a new procedure. In this case, the supervised threshold could also need to be increased. Action to be taken if the measurement exceeds its supervised threshold: Investigate why that many #LSA#s exist. The network might need to be redesigned. Consider using OSPF NSSA to reduce the number of #LSA#s.

This measurement provides the total number of autonomous system border routers reachable within this area. This number is initially zero, and is calculated in each #SPF# pass. Exceeding this limit is at the risk of the operator. Action to be taken if the measurement exceeds its supervised threshold: Investigate why so many external #LSA#s exist and what entity in the network that announces them. The network might need to be redesigned. If OSPF NSSA is not used within the area, consider using it to reduce the number of external #LSA#s.

PmGroup.description: This PmGroup defines measurement types within the OverloadProtection area.

MeasurementType.description: This measurement provides the number of ignored messages related to connections on the #AP#s. The counter is incremented when a request to an existing connection (the #MS#/#UE# is known in the #SGSN-MME# but is not doing any control signaling currently) is ignored on an #AP#. This forces the initiator to resend the message. The reason can be high #CPU# load, high memory consumption on the #AP#s, or both. High #CPU# load is visible in the CPU counters or detected internally in SGSN-MME as long queue length to certain processes. Long queues can occur even if the #CPU# counter is not high, especially if the signaling comes in bursts. Action to be taken if the measurement exceeds its supervised threshold: This is an indication of overload and it is time to offload the #SGSN-MME#, for example, by moving one or more #BSC#s, #RNC#s, or eNodeBs to a less loaded #SGSN-MME#. The threshold for this measurement type indicates a severe overload condition in the #SGSN-MME#. Overload can also occur after an #SGSN-MME# restart or recovery situation after a SW or HW fault. In this case the signaling rate can be so high that the system temporarily needs to reject signaling to protect the local #AP# from overload. It can also happen after restarts of external nodes when #SGSN-MME# needs to take immediate action, such as, eNodeB restart or #HLR#/#HSS# restart, or when external nodes regain connectivity, which can increase signaling due to resending information in the network. The alarm is cleared when the overload situation has ceased. For more information, see #Troubleshooting#.

This measurement provides the number of ignored messages related to connections on the #AP#s. The counter is incremented when a request to a new connection (the #MS#/#UE# that is unknown in the #SGSN-MME#) is ignored on an #AP#. This will lead to, for example, a failed attach or #ISRAU#. The reason can be high #CPU# load, high memory consumption on the #AP#s, or both. High #CPU# load is visible in the #CPU# counters or detected internally in #SGSN-MME# as long queue length to certain processes. Long queues can occur even if the #CPU# counter is not high, especially if the signaling comes in bursts. The reason can be also lack of memory resources on a payload #DP#. The limit is set either by the #AP# handling the connection or by the payload #DP#s with the least free memory. Action to be taken if the measurement exceeds its supervised threshold: This is an indication of overload and it is time to offload the #SGSN-MME#, for example, by moving one or more #BSC#s, #RNC#s, or eNodeBs to a less loaded #SGSN-MME#. If several new connections are ignored, this could be an indication that it is time to reconfigure the network. The threshold for ignored new connections is lower than for existing connections. Overload can also occur after an #SGSN-MME# restart or recovery situation after a SW or HW fault. In this case, the signaling rate can be so high that the system temporarily needs to reject signaling to protect the local #AP# from overload. It can also happen after restarts of external nodes when #SGSN-MME# needs to take immediate action, such as, eNodeB restart or #HLR#/#HSS# restart, or when external nodes regain connectivity, which can increase signaling due to resending information in the network. The alarm is cleared when the overload situation has ceased. For more information, see #Troubleshooting#.

PmGroup.description: This PmGroup defines measurement types within the OverloadProtection_ApOlpPriority area. The AP OLP Priority is set based on the best ARP level for attached UE and is stored in the UE EMM Context. The SGSN-MME uses an AP OLP Priority of 16 for unattached UE. However, both attached and unattached UE can qualify for a specific OLP Priority by indicating one of the following RRC Establishment causes in an Initial UE message sent over the S1-MME Interface:Emergency - OLP Priority based on local Emergency configuration in the SGSN-MMEHigh Priority Access - OLP Priority based on local MPS configuration in the SGSN-MMEDelay Tolerant Access - OLP Priority 17

MeasurementType.description: This indexed measurement shows the number of messages discarded by the Application Processor OverLoad Protection (AP OLP). The index is the AP OLP Priority level assigned to the UE. The AP OLP mechanism discards messages based on OLP Priority levels. There are two measurements related to this measurement: gsnOverloadProtectionIgnoredExistingConnections which provides the number of discarded messages for UE having an existing connection i.e. is known in the MME. This measurement is independant of the OLP Priority level and is overlapping the measurement gsnOverloadProtectionIgnoredConnections. gsnOverloadProtectionIgnoredNewConnections which provides the number of discarded messages for UE that does not have an existing connection i.e. is unknown in the MME. This measurement is independant of the OLP Priority level and is overlapping the measurement gsnOverloadProtectionIgnoredConnections.

PmGroup.description: This PmGroup defines measurement types within the OverloadProtection_E_PIU area.

MeasurementType.description: This measurement provides the number of refused incoming S1AP requests. The counter is incremented when an incoming request is subject to OLP for the S1-MME interface. This will for example lead to failed Attach, Detach, Service Request or TAU. The OLP for the S1-MME interface is active on the SCTP devices. Action to be taken if the measurement exceeds its supervised threshold: This is an indication of signaling overload in SGSN-MME. Consider reviewing the network dimensioning/configuration. Note that the overload could be due to a temporary error in the network. Examples of this could be SGSN-MME restart, large restart or an eNodeB restart. It may also occur during temporary external communication problems towards for example the HLR/HSS, when causing the mobiles to retry their signaling (mainly attach) in a large scale. In this case the signaling rate may be so high that the system temporarily needs to ignore it to protect the APs from overload. The alarm will be cleared as more and more subscribers are successfully attached and/or have successfully finished their signaling towards the SGSN-MME, which results in decreased signaling load. If the reason for the alarm is temporary and well known, no actions need to be taken. For further details see Troubleshooting. Moving one or more BSCs or RNCs (SGSN-MME deployment dependent) may also improve the situation, due to the fact that if the SGSN-MME is heavily loaded from the GSM or WCDMA side it affects the total load on the SGSN-MME, thus may decrease the signaling success on the LTE side also. When this alarm is raised and not cleared within a limited period of time, it could be an indication that it is time to reconfigure the network.

PmGroup.description: This PmGroup defines measurement types within the OverloadProtection_MM area.

MeasurementType.description: This measurement provides the number of #S1AP# paging messages that have been discarded by the #SCTP# paging overload protection mechanism in order to avoid a potential overload of the #SCTP# front end #PIU#s. Note that as long as the #CPU# load is not extremely high only a subset of the paging messages is discarded, and hence the paging procedure does not necessarily fail. Outgoing paging messages related to CS Fallback to WCDMA and GSM are not discarded by the #OLP# mechanism. Action to be taken if the measurement exceeds its supervised threshold: This is an indication of overload and it is time to offload the #SGSN-MME#, for example, by moving one or more eNodeBs to a less loaded #SGSN-MME#. If several paging messages are ignored, this could be an indication that it is time to reconfigure the network. The alarm is cleared when the overload situation has ceased. For more information, see #Troubleshooting#.
This measurement provides the total number of outgoing GTP-C request messages that have been rejected by the outbound overload protection mechanism.
This measurement provides the total number of outgoing request messages toward the HSS that have been rejected by the outbound overload protection mechanism.

PmGroup.description: This PmGroup defines measurement types within the OverloadProtection_Ss7OlpPriority area.The overload protection priority as given by primitives from the MAP, CAP, BSSAP+ or RANAP layers. (1 = highest priority and 5 = lowest priority.)

MeasurementType.description: This measurement provides the number of rejected outgoing request through #SS7# link. The counter is incremented when an outgoing request through #SS7# link is rejected. #SCCP# messages are discarded. #TCAP# messages are rejected with a reject message. Action to be taken if the measurement exceeds its supervised threshold: This is an indication of #SS7# overload. The #SS7# bandwidth may need to be increased or the Ss7EffectiveBandwidth parameter may need to be adjusted to match available #SS7# bandwidth. #SS7# overload may also occur after an #SGSN-MME# restart or a large restart, and the reattach rate may be so high that the system temporarily needs to reject #SS7# traffic to protect #SS7# links from overload. The alarm will be cleared as more and more subscribers are successfully attached in the #SGSN-MME# which results in decreased load on the #SS7# links. For more information, see #Troubleshooting#.

PmGroup.description: This PmGroup defines measurement types within the OverloadProtection_U_PIU area.

MeasurementType.description: This measurement provides the number of refused incoming #SCCP# connection requests. The counter is incremented when an incoming request is subject to the #SS7# #OLP# for Incoming Traffic. This will lead to failed Attach, Detach, Service Request or #RAU#. The #SS7# #OLP# for incoming traffic is active on the #SS7# devices. Action to be taken if the measurement exceeds its supervised threshold: This is an indication of signaling overload in #SGSN-MME#. It may be time to offload the #SGSN-MME#, for example by moving one or more #RNC#s to an #SGSN-MME# with less signaling load. This alarm is raised only for connection oriented #SCCP# signaling for #WCDMA#. However moving one or more #BSC#s may also improve the situation, due to the fact that if the #SGSN-MME# is heavily loaded from the #GSM# side it affects the total load on the #SGSN-MME#, thus may decrease the signaling success on the #WCDMA# side also. When this alarm is raised and not cleared within a limited period of time, it could be an indication that it is time to reconfigure the network. Overload may also occur after a #SGSN-MME# restart, large restart or an #RNC# restart. It may also occur during temporary external communication problems towards for example the #HLR#, when causing the mobiles to retry their signaling (mainly attach) in a large scale. In this case the signaling rate may be so high that the system temporarily needs to ignore it to protect the #AP#s from overload. The alarm will be cleared as more and more subscribers are successfully attached and/or have successfully finished their signaling towards the #SGSN-MME#, which results in decreased signaling load. If the reason for the alarm is temporary and well known, no actions need to be taken. For further details see #Troubleshooting#.

MeasurementType.description: This measurement provides the number of times the #SCTP# user requested the #SCTP# to close an association to a remote endpoint by sending the #SCTP# Abort Request primitive.

This measurement provides the number of times the #SCTP# Association Restart Indication primitive has been received from the #SCTP# to indicate that the #SCTP# has detected that the remote endpoint restarted the association.

This measurement provides the number of times the #SCTP# Association Confirmation primitive has been received from #SCTP# to confirm that the #SCTP# tried to establish the association earlier requested by the #SCTP# user.
This measurement provides the number of times the #SCTP# user tried to establish an association by sending the #SCTP# Association Request primitive.

This measurement provides the number of times the #SCTP# Communication Error Indication primitive has been received from the #SCTP# to indicate that the #SCTP# received an error chunk from its remote endpoint and decided to notify the #SCTP# user.

This measurement provides the number of times the #SCTP# Communication Lost Indication primitive has been received from the #SCTP# to inform when the #SCTP# lost communication with an endpoint completely or detected an abort or a shutdown operation from the remote endpoint.

This measurement provides the number of times the #SCTP# Communication Up Indication primitive is received by the #SCTP# user to indicate when the #SCTP# became ready to send or receive #SCTP# User messages, or when a lost communication to a remote endpoint was restored.

This measurement provides the number of times the #SCTP# Congestion Indication primitive has been received from the #SCTP# to indicate that the remote endpoint is inaccessible due to failure or congestion. #SCTP# user traffic cannot be sent to this remote endpoint for the moment.

PmGroup.description: This PmGroup defines measurement types within the SRNSRelocation_U area.

MeasurementType.description: This measurement provides the number of attempted Inter-SGSN SRNS Relocation procedures counted in the old SGSN. The counter is incremented when the old SGSN receives an Inter SGSN SRNS "Relocation Required" message from the source RNC. The number of attempted Inter-SGSN Relocation from S4-SGSN to Gn-SGSN is also counted.

This measurement provides the number of attempted Inter-SGSN SRNS Relocation procedures and inter SGSN/MME IRAT handover procedures from #LTE# access to #UMTS# access counted in the new SGSN . The counter is incremented when the new SGSN receives an SRNS "Forward Relocation Request" message from the old SGSN or old MME.

This measurement provides the number of attempted Inter-SGSN SRNS Relocation for a UE using S4 mode counted in the new SGSN. The counter is incremented when the new SGSN receives a "Forward Relocation Request" message from the old SGSN.

This measurement provides the number of attempted Inter-SGSN SRNS Relocation for a UE using S4 mode counted in the old SGSN. The counter is incremented when the old SGSN receives an Inter S4-SGSN SRNS "Relocation Required" message from the source RNC and the target RA is served by a new SGSN.

This measurement provides the number of attempted Intra-SGSN SRNS Relocation procedures. The counter is incremented when the SGSN receives an Intra-SGSN SRNS "Relocation Required" message from the source RNC.

This measurement provides the number of attempted Intra-SGSN SRNS Relocation for a UE using S4 mode. The counter is incremented when the SGSN receives an Intra S4-SGSN SRNS "Relocation Required" message from the source RNC and the target RA is served by the same SGSN.

This measurement provides the number of failed Inter-SGSN SRNS Relocation procedures counted in the old SGSN. The counter is incremented when the old SGSN receives an Inter SGSN SRNS "Relocation Required" message from the RNC and the relocation procedure fails to continue due to internal reasons or when the old SGSN receives a "Forward Relocation Response" message but not all of the needed RABs are allocated in the new SGSN. The number of failed Inter-SGSN Relocation from S4-SGSN to Gn-SGSN is also counted. The counter is not incremented when old S4-SGSN receives a "Forward Relocation Response" message but not all of the needed RABs are allocated in the new Gn-SGSN.

This measurement provides the number of failed Inter SGSN SRNS Relocation procedures for a UE using S4 mode counted in the old SGSN. The counter is incremented when the old SGSN receives an Inter S4-SGSN SRNS "Relocation Required" message from the source RNC, the target RA is served by a new SGSN, and the relocation procedure fails to continue due to internal reasons.

This measurement provides the number of failed Intra-SGSN SRNS Relocation procedures and intra-SGSN/MME IRAT handover procedures from #LTE# access to #UMTS# access. The counter is incremented when the SGSN receives an Intra-SGSN SRNS "Relocation Required" message from the RNC and the relocation procedure fails to continue due to internal reasons or when the SGSN receives a "Relocation Request Acknowledge" message from the target RNC but some of the needed RABs failed to set up.

This measurement provides the number of failed Intra SGSN SRNS Relocation procedures for a UE using S4 mode. The counter is incremented when the SGSN receives an Intra S4-SGSN SRNS "Relocation Required" message from the source RNC, the target RA is served by the same SGSN, and the relocation procedure fails to continue due to internal reasons.

This measurement provides the number of successful Inter-SGSN SRNS Relocation procedures counted in the old SGSN. The counter is incremented when the old SGSN receives a "Forward Relocation Complete" message from the new SGSN. The number of successful Inter-SGSN Relocation from S4-SGSN to Gn-SGSN is also counted.

This measurement provides the number of successful Inter-SGSN SRNS Relocation procedures and inter SGSN/MME IRAT handover procedures from #LTE# access to #UMTS# access . The counter is incremented when the new SGSN receives a "Forward Relocation Complete Acknowledge" message from the old SGSN or old MME, or the new SGSN fails to receive the "Forward Relocation Complete Acknowledge" message due to GTP message timeout after N3 timeouts and resendings.

This measurement provides the number of successful Inter SGSN SRNS Relocation for a UE using S4 mode counted in the new SGSN. The counter is incremented when the new SGSN receives a "Relocation Complete" message from the target RNC.

This measurement provides the number of successful Inter-SGSN SRNS Relocation for a UE using S4 mode counted in the old SGSN. The counter is incremented when the old SGSN receives a "Forward Relocation Complete Notification" message from the new SGSN.

This measurement provides the number of successful Intra-SGSN SRNS Relocation procedures and intra-SGSN/MME IRAT handover procedures from #LTE# access to #UMTS# access. The counter is incremented when the SGSN receives a "Relocation Complete" message from the target RNC.

This measurement provides the number of successful Intra-SGSN SRNS Relocation for a UE using S4 mode. The counter is incremented when the SGSN receives a "Relocation Complete" message from the target RNC.

MeasurementType.description: This measurement provides the number of #MSU# messages received on this broadband link. The maximum read interval is 900 sec.
MeasurementType.alarmRaiseDefaultLevel: 1. Note that when supervision is activated, use a value that is 90% of the configured association bandwidth @ 150 byte packet size [packets]. If the calculated value equals 0, the level should be set to 1.
MeasurementType.alarmClearDefaultLevel: 0. Note that when supervision is activated, use a value that is 80% of the configured association bandwidth @ 150 byte packet size [packets].

MeasurementType.description: This measurement provides the number of #MSU# messages sent on this broadband link. The maximum read interval is 900 sec.

This measurement provides the number of #MSU# messages sent on this narrowband link. The maximum read interval is 1800 sec.
This measurement provides the bandwidth usage (in percent) for the #MTP-L2# receive link. The value is a mean value of the link load since the last reading of the gauge value.
This measurement provides the bandwidth usage (in percent) for the #MTP-L2# transmit link. The value is a mean value of the link load since the last reading of the gauge value.
This measurement provides the number of KB received by MTP-L3 on a narrowband link. The maximum read interval is 10800 sec.
This measurement provides the number of KB sent by MTP-L3 on a narrowband link. The maximum read interval is 10800 sec.
#SL# failure is detected on a narrowband link. This counter shows the index for where the link is connected.
#SL# restoration has occurred on a narrowband link. The counter shows the index for where the link is connected.

MeasurementType.description: The #MSU# is discarded due to routing data error. The message could not be routed and was therefore discarded.;The standard routing label contains the destination and originating point of the message, along with the signaling link selection (used for selecting which signaling link to use). One of these fields was invalid in the message received from the user part.;Inspection of the log file may show the content of the invalid message field, received from the MTP-L3 user, and clarify the cause of the error.

This measurement provides the number of discarded #MSU# packets received. The packets are discarded by the #OPC# screening when the received OPC is not accepted. The #ss7M3MSUDiscardedOPCScreening# event includes both the received #OPC# and the adjacent #DPC#.
MeasurementType.alarmRaiseDefaultLevel: 1. Note that when supervision is activated, use a value that is 1% of the configured signaling link or the association bandwidth @ 150 byte packet size [packets]. If the calculated value equals 0, set the level to 1.

MeasurementType.description: This measurement provides the total number of running dialogues.
This measurement provides the total number of running operations.
A protocol error is detected in component portion.

A protocol error has occurred, since P-abort is unrecognized message type.
The adjacent #SP# is inaccessible.

This measurement provides the total number of Transaction Capability (TC) messages sent by the stack.

This measurement provides the total number of terminated #UDTS# messages per local signaling point.

This measurement provides the total number of terminated #XUDTS# messages per local signaling point.
