PmGroup.description: This PmGroup defines measurement types within the SS7_RemoteSP area.

MeasurementType.description: This measurement provides the number of times the #ASPAC# Acknowledge message has been received from the remote #M3UA# peer to acknowledge an #ASPAC# message earlier sent from this #M3UA#.
This measurement provides the number of times #M3UA# acknowledged a received #ASPAC# message by sending an #ASPAC# Acknowledge message to the remote #M3UA# peer.
This measurement provides the number of times #ASPAC# has been received from the remote #M3UA# peer, which is a request for #M3UA# to take the Signaling Process from state Inactive to state Active.
This measurement provides the number of times #M3UA# requested the remote Signaling Process (SP) to move from state Inactive to state Active by sending the #ASPAC# message.
This measurement provides the number of times the #ASPDN# Acknowledge message has been received from the remote #M3UA# peer to acknowledge an #ASPDN# message earlier sent from this #M3UA#.
This measurement provides the number of times #M3UA# acknowledged a received #ASPDN# message by sending an #ASPDN# Acknowledge message to the remote #M3UA# peer.
This measurement provides the number of times #ASPDN# has been received from the remote #M3UA# peer, which is a request for #M3UA# to take the Signaling Process from state Inactive to state Down.
This measurement provides the number of times #M3UA# requested the remote Signaling Processor to move from state Inactive to state Down by sending the #ASPDN# message.
This measurement provides the number of times the #ASPIA# Acknowledge message has been received from the remote #M3UA# peer to acknowledge an #ASPIA# message earlier sent from this #M3UA#.
This measurement provides the number of times #M3UA# acknowledged a received #ASPIA# message by sending an #ASPIA# Acknowledge message to the remote #M3UA# peer.
This measurement provides the number of times #ASPIA# has been received from the remote #M3UA# peer, which is a request for #M3UA# to take the Signaling Process from state Active to state Inactive.
This measurement provides the number of times #M3UA# requested the remote Signaling Process to move from state Active to state Inactive by sending the #ASPIA# message.
This measurement provides the number of times the #ASPUP# Acknowledge message has been received from the remote #M3UA# peer to acknowledge an #ASPUP# message earlier sent from this #M3UA#.
This measurement provides the number of times #M3UA# acknowledged a received #ASPUP# message by sending an #ASPUP# Acknowledge message to the remote #M3UA# peer.
This measurement provides the number of times #ASPUP# has been received from the remote #M3UA# peer, which is a request to the #M3UA# to take the Signaling Process from state Down to state Inactive.
This measurement provides the number of times #M3UA# requested the remote Signaling Process to move from state Down to state Inactive by sending the #ASPUP# message.

This measurement provides the number of times the #M3UA# #DAUD# message has been received from #ASP# to request #SS7# destination audit for the #SG#/#SGP#. #SGSN# does not support being an #SGP#, so this counter should always be 0.
This measurement provides the number of times the #M3UA# #DAUD# message has been sent from #M3UA# #ASP# to request #SS7# destination audit for an #SG#/#SGP#.
This measurement provides the number of times the #M3UA# #DAVA# message has been received from the Remote #SGP# to inform that one or more #SS7# destinations are available.

This measurement provides the number of times the #M3UA# #DAVA# message has been sent from #M3UA# #ASP# or IP Signaling Process in response to a #DAUD# message. #SGSN# does not support being #SGP#, so this counter should always be 0.
This measurement provides the number of times the #M3UA# #DRST# message has been received from the #SG# to inform that one or more #SS7# destinations are restricted.

This measurement provides the number of times the #M3UA# #DRST# message has been sent from #SG# to inform that one or more #SS7# destinations are now restricted. #SGSN# does not support acting as an #SGP#, so the counter should always be 0.
This measurement provides the number of times the #M3UA# #DUNA# message has been received from the Remote #SGP# to inform that one or more #SS7# destinations are unreachable.

This measurement provides the number of times the #M3UA# #DUNA# message has been sent from #M3UA# #ASP#/#IPSP# in response to a #DAUD# message. #SGSN# does not support being #SGP#, so this counter should always be 0.
This measurement provides the number of times the #M3UA# #DUPU# message has been received from the Remote #SGP# to inform that a remote peer #MTP-L3# User Part at an #SS7# node is unavailable.

This measurement provides the number of times the #M3UA# #DUPU# message has been sent from an #SGP# to inform that a remote peer #MTP-L3# User Part at an #SS7# node is unavailable. #SGSN# does not support being #SGP#, so this counter should always be 0.

This measurement provides the number of times the #M3UA# Error message has been received from the Remote Signaling Process to inform #M3UA# of an error event associated with an incoming message (for example Invalid Parameter Value).

This measurement provides the number of times the #M3UA# Error message has been sent from #M3UA# to inform the Remote Signaling Process of an error event associated with an incoming message (for example Invalid Parameter Value).
This measurement provides the number of times the #M3UA# #NTFY# message has been received from the Remote #SGP#/#IPSP# to inform that the state of the remote #AS# has been changed.
This measurement provides the number of times the #M3UA# #NTFY# message has been sent from #M3UA#/#IPSP# to inform all remote #ASPs# that the state of this #AS# has changed.
This measurement provides the number of #MSUs# received from remote Signaling Process. The maximum read interval is 900 sec.
MeasurementType.alarmRaiseDefaultLevel: 1. Note that when supervision is activated, use a value that is 90% of the configured association bandwidth @ 150 byte packet size [packets]. If the calculated value equals 0, the level should be set to 1.
MeasurementType.alarmClearDefaultLevel: 0. Note that when supervision is activated, use a value that is 80% of the configured association bandwidth @ 150 byte packet size [packets].

MeasurementType.description: This measurement provides the number of #MSUs# sent to remote Signaling Process. The maximum read interval is 900 sec.
MeasurementType.alarmRaiseDefaultLevel: 1. Note that when supervision is activated, use a value that is 90% of the configured association bandwidth @ 150 byte packet size [packets]. If the calculated value equals 0, the level should be set to 1.
MeasurementType.alarmClearDefaultLevel: 0. Note that when supervision is activated, use a value that is 80% of the configured association bandwidth @ 150 byte packet size [packets].

MeasurementType.description: This measurement provides the number of KB received from remote Signaling Process. The maximum read interval is 3600 sec.

MeasurementType.alarmClearDefaultLevel: 0. Note that when supervision is activated, use a value that is 80% of the configured association bandwidth.

MeasurementType.description: This measurement provides the number of KB sent to remote Signaling Process. The maximum read interval is 3600 sec.
MeasurementType.alarmRaiseDefaultLevel: 1. Note that when supervision is activated, use a value that is 90% of the configured association bandwidth. If the calculated value equals 0, the level should be set to 1.
MeasurementType.alarmClearDefaultLevel: 0. Note that when supervision is activated, use a value that is 80% of the configured association bandwidth.

MeasurementType.description: This measurement provides the number of times the Remote Signaling Process has become available for User Part traffic (association moved to active state).
This measurement provides the number of times the Remote Signaling Process has become unavailable for User Part traffic (association moved from active state).
This measurement provides the number of times #M3UA# requested that the #SCTP# should close an association by sending the #SCTP# Abort Request message.

This measurement provides the number of times the #SCTP# Association Restart Indication message has been received from #SCTP# to indicate that the #SCTP# has detected that the remote peer restarted the association.

This measurement provides the number of times the #SCTP# Association Confirmation message has been received from #SCTP# to confirm that the #SCTP# tried to establish the association earlier requested by M3UA.
This measurement provides the number of times #M3UA# tried to establish an association by sending the #SCTP# Association Request message.

This measurement provides the number of times the #SCTP# Communication Error Indication message has been received from #SCTP# to indicate that #SCTP# received an Error chunk from its peer and decided to notify #M3UA#.

This measurement provides the number of times the #SCTP# Communication Lost Indication message has been received from #SCTP# to inform when #SCTP# lost communication with an endpoint completely or detected an abort or a shutdown operation from the endpoint.

This measurement provides the number of times the #SCTP# Communication Up Indication message is received by #M3UA# to indicate when #SCTP# became ready to send or receive #M3UA# messages, or when a lost communication to an endpoint was restored.

This measurement provides the number of times the #SCTP# Congestion Indication message has been received from #SCTP# to indicate that the remote Signaling Process is inaccessible due to failure or congestion. #M3UA# traffic cannot be sent to this destination for the moment.

This measurement provides the number of times the #SCTP# Failure Indication message has been received from #SCTP# to indicate that #SCTP# has encountered a problem when trying to send a message, earlier requested by #M3UA#.

This measurement provides the number of times the #SCTP# Shutdown Confirmation message has been received from #SCTP# to confirm that the shutdown process, earlier requested from #M3UA#, has started successfully or not.
This measurement provides the number of times the #M3UA# tried to close an association by sending the #SCTP# Shutdown Request message.

This measurement provides the number of times the #SCTP# Status Confirmation message has been received from #SCTP# to inform #M3UA# about the current status of the endpoint, requested earlier by #M3UA#.
This measurement provides the number of times #M3UA# requested that the #SCTP# should return the current status of the endpoint by sending the #SCTP# Status Request message.

This measurement provides the number of Data Form 1 messages received (Connection Oriented data). It is registered for SGSN (G) if the NumberOfConnections SCCP parameter is > 0 for any local SAP instance, but it is not applicable for SGSN (G).

This measurement provides the number of Released messages received. It is registered for SGSN (G) if the NumberOfConnections SCCP parameter is > 0 for any local SAP instance, but it is not applicable for SGSN (G).

This measurement provides the number of successful Dedicated Bearer Activation procedures between the #MME# and the #UE#.
