This measurement provides the number of APN redirections to the subscribed default APN per MME.

This measurement provides the number of Dedicated Bearer Deactivation procedures attempted by the #MME#. The counter is not incremented when resending a Deactivate EPS Bearer Context Request to the #UE#.
This measurement provides the number of successful Dedicated Bearer Deactivation procedures initiated by the #MME#.

This measurement provides the number of attempted #EPS# Bearer Modification procedures initiated by the #MME#. The counter is incremented when the Modify #EPS# Bearer Context Request message is transmitted to the #UE#.

This measurement provides the number of successful #EPS# Bearer Modification procedures initiated by the #MME#. The counter is incremented when the Modify #EPS# Bearer Context Accept message arrives at the #MME#.

This measurement provides the number of successfully completed EPS Bearer Activation procedures with no IPv4 address in the PGW control plane or user plane. #Note: Both default bearer and dedicated bearer procedures are counted.Note#

This measurement provides the number of Dedicated Bearer Activation procedure attempts between the #MME# and the #UE# for #IMS# emergency service. The counter is not incremented when resending an Activate Dedicated EPS Bearer Context Request to the #UE#.
This measurement provides the number of successful Dedicated Bearer Activation procedures between the #MME# and the #UE# for #IMS# emergency service.

This measurement provides the number of Dedicated Bearer Activation procedure attempts for GBR bearers between the MME and the UE. The counter is not incremented when resending an Activate Dedicated EPS Bearer Context Request for GBR bearers to the UE.
This measurement provides the number of successful Dedicated Bearer Activation procedures for GBR bearers between the MME and the UE.

This measurement provides the number of attempted default #EPS# Bearer Activation procedures between #MME# and #UE# for #IMS# emergency service. The counter is not incremented when resending an Activate Default EPS Bearer Context Request to the #UE#.
This measurement provides the number of successfully completed default #EPS# Bearer Activation procedures towards #UE# for #IMS# emergency service.
This measurement provides the number of Activate Default EPS Bearer Context Request messages. The counter is increased whenever this message is sent from the MME to the UE.
This measurement provides the number of Activate Default EPS Bearer Context Accept messages. The counter is increased whenever this message is sent from the UE to the MME.
This measurement provides the number of attempted #EPS# Bearer Activation procedures. #Note:Only default bearer procedures are counted.Note#
This measurement provides the number of #EPS# bearers, both default and dedicated, that are disconnected by the #UE#.
For each Dedicated #EPS# Bearer Activation request sent on S11 to the #MME#, this counter is incremented with the number of bearers included in the request.

For each Dedicated #EPS# Bearer Activation attempt sent to the #MME#, this counter is incremented with the number of bearers that were not activated because the UE was in suspend status, and the MME was unable to page the UE. A response with cause code 102 (Unable to page UE due to Suspension) is returned to the #SGW#.

For each Dedicated #EPS# Bearer Activation attempt sent to the #MME#, this counter is incremented with the number of bearers, that were not activated, because the feature 'Dedicated bearers' is 'Off.' A response with cause code 68 (Service not supported) is returned to the Serving Gateway. (Please note that this counter does not affect any KPI.)

For each Dedicated #EPS# Bearer Activation attempt sent to the #MME#, this counter is incremented with the number of bearers, that were not activated, due to that the #UE# does not respond or due to that MME is unable to page the UE. A response with cause code 87 (UE not responding) or cause code 90 (Unable to page UE) is returned to the Serving Gateway.

For each Dedicated #EPS# Bearer Activation attempt sent to the #MME#, this counter is incremented with the number of bearers, that were not activated, due to that the #UE# rejects the activation attempt. A response with cause code 88 (UE refuses) is returned to the Serving Gateway.
For each Dedicated #EPS# Bearer Activation request sent on S11 to the #MME#, this counter is incremented with the number of successfully activated bearers included in the request.

This measurement provides the number of Create Session Request messages. The counter is increased whenever this message is sent from the MME to the SGW. The Create Session Request message might include one default bearer and multiple dedicated bearers.
This measurement provides the number of Create Session Response messages with cause code 16 (Request accepted). The counter is increased whenever the MME receives this message from the SGW.
This measurement provides the number of attempted Dedicated Bearer Deactivation procedures received from the Serving Gateway.
This measurement provides the number of successful Dedicated Bearer Deactivation procedures sent to the Serving Gateway.

This measurement provides the amount of stand-alone PDN Connectivity Request messages with emergency indication discarded by the MME due to UE Signaling Control. The counter increases if a message is discarded when the UE Signaling Control rule is in measurement and control mode. Messages are discarded if the value of the ThresholdNumber parameter is exceeded within a measurement interval. The ThresholdNumber parameter is configured in the UE Signaling Control rule.
This measurement provides the number of times that the S1TGBRBearerDeactivation timer is cancelled.
This measurement provides the number of times that the S1TGBRBearerDeactivation timer expires.
This measurement provides the number of times that the UE reconnects before the S1TGBRBearerDeactivation timer expires.

This measurement provides the number of attempted Modify Bearer Command procedures initiated by the MME. Note: The measured data of the counter is incremented when Modify Bearer Command message is sent from the MME.

This measurement provides the number of successful responses of Modify Bearer Command procedures received from SGW. Note: The measured data of the counter is incremented when Update Bearer Request message is received from SGW in response to Modify Bearer Command.

This measurement provides the number of attempted Bearer Modification procedures initiated by the #PDN# Gateway. The counter is incremented when the Update Bearer Request message arrives at the #MME#. This message may contain multiple bearers, each bearer is cumulated to the counter.

This measurement provides the number of successful Bearer Modification procedures initiated by the #PDN# Gateway. The counter is incremented when the Update Bearer Response message is sent to the Serving Gateway. This message may contain multiple bearers. Each bearer with an indication of a successful bearer update is cumulated to the counter.

This measurement provides the number of active #EPS# bearers, that is, the gauge is incremented when a new #EPS# bearer is activated and decremented when an #EPS# bearer is deactivated. #Note:Both default and dedicated bearers are counted.Note#

This measurement provides the number of active #EPS# bearers established for #IMS# Emergency Service, that is, the gauge is incremented when a new #EPS# bearer is activated for #IMS# Emergency Service and decremented when an #EPS# bearer for #IMS# Emergency Service is deactivated. #Note:Both default and dedicated bearers for #IMS# Emergency Service are counted.Note#

This measurement provides the number of active default #EPS# bearers, that is, the gauge is incremented when a new default #EPS# bearer is activated and decremented when a default #EPS# bearer is deactivated.

This measurement provides the number of active default #EPS# bearers for #IMS# emergency service, that is, the gauge is incremented when a new default #EPS# bearer is activated for #IMS# Emergency Service and decremented when a default #EPS# bearer for #IMS# Emergency Service is deactivated.

This measurement provides the amount of PDN Connectivity Request messages that are controlled by the UE Signaling Control feature with the detach action. The counter applies only when the UE Signaling Control feature is activated in the Measurement and Control mode. The counter is increased whenever a PDN Connectivity Request message is identified and controlled by UE Signaling Control with the detach action during a control period.

This measurement provides the amount of stand-alone PDN Connectivity Request messages discarded by the MME due to UE Signaling Control. The counter increases if a message is discarded when the UE Signaling Control rule is in measurement and control mode. Messages are discarded if the value of the ThresholdNumber parameter is exceeded within a measurement interval. The ThresholdNumber parameter is configured in the UE Signaling Control rule.

This measurement provides the amount of PDN Connectivity Request messages that are controlled by the UE Signaling Control feature with the reject action. The counter applies only when the UE Signaling Control feature is activated in the Measurement and Control mode. The counter is increased whenever a PDN Connectivity Request message is identified and controlled by UE Signaling Control with the reject action during a control period.

This measurement provides the number of eNodeB-initiated S1 releases due to the "Radio Connection With UE Lost" cause when the UE has GBR bearers. When the TimerBasedGBRBearerDeactivation parameter is set to true, this measurement also provides the number of times that the S1TGbrBearerDeactivation timer is started.
This measurement provides the number of successfully completed #EPS# Bearer Activation procedures. #Note:Only default bearer procedures are counted.Note#
This measurement provides the number of successfully completed #EPS# Bearer Deactivation procedures for both default and dedicated bearers.

This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful #EPS# Bearer Activation procedures, for each #MME#, that occur due to cause code 27 (Unknown or missing access point name), and cause code 28 (Unknown PDN address or PDN type). The counter is incremented when the #MME# receives corresponding failure causes from the Serving Gateway. #Note:Only default bearer procedures are counted.Note#

This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful #EPS# bearer activation procedures for each #MME# that occur due to cause code 32 (Service option not supported), and cause code 33 (Requested Service Option not subscribed). The counter is incremented if the #PDN# Type is not supported or if the request is denied in the #MME# due to subscriber data restriction. #Note:Only default bearer procedures are counted.Note#

PmGroup.description: This PmGroup defines measurement types within the Session_SM_G area.

MeasurementType.description: This measurement provides the number of #APN# redirections to the SGSN default APN per SGSN.
This measurement provides the number of APN redirections to the subscribed APN of the lowest context ID when using EPS subscription data per SGSN.

This measurement provides the number of #APN# redirections to the subscribed APN per SGSN. #Note: If the SGSN default APN included in the subscribed data is used as the negotiated APN, this counter will exclude this scenario. Note#
This measurement provides the number of APN redirections to the subscribed default APN when using EPS subscription data per SGSN.

This measurement provides the number of attempted primary #PDP# context activation procedures. These include the static as well as the dynamic #PDP# addresses. The counter is incremented at the moment when SGSN identifies the message as a #RIL#3 Activate #PDP# Context Request message.
MeasurementType.alarmRaiseDefaultLevel: value of 1% of attach limit (hard limit)
MeasurementType.alarmClearDefaultLevel: value of 0.5% of attach limit (hard limit)

MeasurementType.description: This measurement provides the number of attempted primary #PDP# context activation requests where a dynamic #PDP# address is required to be used.
Number of attempted primary #PDP# Context Activation procedures per #SGSN# for home subscribers. Home subscribers are defined by the roaming status parameter during the #IMSI#-series configuration.

This measurement provides the amount of Primary PDP Context Activation messages that are discarded by UE Signaling Control. Incremented when UE Signaling Control is activated, and when it identifies an Activate PDP Context Request message during a control period. Applies to GSM systems only.
This measurement provides the number of attempted MS-Initiated and Network-Requested Secondary #PDP# context activation procedures.
This measurement provides the number of attempted Network Requested Secondary #PDP# context activations.
This measurement provides the number of Network Requested Secondary #PDP# context activation requests accepted by an MS.
This measurement provides the number of #PDP# context that is disconnected by the #GGSN#. A message can handle more than one PDP context, then the TDI-flag is 1.
This measurement provides the number of #PDP# context that is disconnected by the #MS#. A message can handle more than one PDP context, then the TDI-flag is 1.

This measurement provides the number of #PDP# context that is disconnected by the #SGSN#. Note that the counter is incremented according to standard and also when sending "Deactivate PDP Context Request" to the #MS# after an "Error indication" is received from the #GGSN#. A message can handle more than one PDP context, then the TDI-flag is 1.

This measurement provides the number of #PDP# context that is disconnected by the #SGSN# where cause code 38 (Network failure) is sent to the #MS#. A message can handle more than one PDP context, then the TDI-flag is 1.

This measurement provides the number of #PDP# contexts that were deactivated by the #SGSN-MME# with cause code #39, "Reactivation Required". The cause code is sent to the #MS#. One message can handle more PDP contexts if the TDI-flag is 1.
This measurement provides the number of attempted PDP context deactivation procedures triggered by the SGSN due to the ODB.
This measurement provides the number of attempted #MS#-Initiated #PDP# context modifications procedures.
This measurement provides the number of attempted #SGSN#-initiated #PDP# context modifications procedures.

This measurement provides the number of attempted #GGSN#-initiated #PDP# context update procedures. An Update #PDP# Context Request message can be sent from a #GGSN# to an #SGSN# to renegotiate the #QoS# of a #PDP# context. Only attempts at #QoS# renegotiation are counted.

This measurement provides the number of attempted #SGSN#-initiated #PDP# context update procedures. An Update PDP Context Request message shall be sent from an #SGSN# to a #GGSN# as part of the #GPRS# inter-#SGSN# routeing update procedure, or the #PDP# context modification procedure. It shall be used to change the #QoS# and the path. The message shall be sent by the new #SGSN# at the inter-#SGSN# routeing update procedure.
This measurement provides the number of deleted PDP contexts in old SGSN instead of transferring to new SGSN, that is when the T3 tunnel expires.

This measurement provides the number of active #PDP# contexts, that is, the gauge is incremented whenever a new #PDP# context is activated and decremented whenever a #PDP# context is deactivated. Note: The triggering and clearing levels needs to be changed manually or by triggering a manual small restart when the #PDP# capacity license value is changed.
MeasurementType.alarmRaiseDefaultLevel: value of 90 % of the PDP capacity license limit
MeasurementType.alarmClearDefaultLevel: value of 85 % of the PDP capacity license limit

MeasurementType.description: This measurement provides the number of subscribers having an activated #PDP# context, that is subscribers that can send and receive #GPRS# packet data. The gauge is incremented when a subscriber activates the first context and decremented when the subscriber deactivates the last context. Note: The triggering and clearing levels needs to be changed manually or by triggering a manual small restart when the #PDP# capacity license value is changed.
MeasurementType.alarmRaiseDefaultLevel: value of 90 % of the PDP capacity license limit
MeasurementType.alarmClearDefaultLevel: value of 85 % of the PDP capacity license limit

MeasurementType.description: This measurement provides the number of PDP contexts deactivated by the old SGSN after the contexts were transferred to the new SGSN. The reason is that the old SGSN aborted the ISRAU procedure when the MS re-entered the old SGSN's service area prior to the old SGSN receiving a CANCEL LOCATION message from the HLR.
This measurement provides the number of successfully completed primary #PDP# context activations. For these context activations, the #GGSN# is updated successfully.
This measurement provides the number of successfully completed primary #PDP# context activations where a dynamic #PDP# address is used.
Number of successful primary #PDP# Context Activation procedures per #SGSN# for home subscribers. Home subscribers are defined by the roaming status parameter during the #IMSI#-series configuration.
This measurement provides the number of successfully completed MS-Initiated and Network-Requested Secondary #PDP# context activations.
This measurement provides the number of successfully completed Network Requested Secondary #PDP# context activations.

This measurement provides the number of successfully handled #PDP# context deactivations initiated by the #GGSN#. For these context deactivations, the #MS# has accepted the #PDP# context deactivation. A message can handle more than one PDP context, then the TDI-flag is 1.

This measurement provides the number of successfully completed #PDP# context deactivations. For these context deactivations, the #GGSN# is updated successfully (that is, deletion of the #PDP# context). A message can handle more than one PDP context, then the TDI-flag is 1.

This measurement provides the number of successfully handled #PDP# context deactivations initiated by the #SGSN#. Note that the counter is incremented according to standard and also when receiving "Delete PDP Context Response" from the #GGSN# for the cases when no "Deactivate PDP Context Response" can be received from the #MS# since no "Deactivate PDP Context Request" was sent to the #MS#. A message can handle more than one PDP context, then the TDI-flag is 1.

This measurement provides the number of successfully handled #MS#-initiated #PDP# context modifications procedures. These modifications are performed successfully when a Modify PDP Context Accept message is sent to the #MS#.

This measurement provides the number of successfully handled #SGSN#-initiated #PDP# context modifications procedures. These modifications are performed successfully when a positive Modify PDP Context Accept message is received from the #MS#.

This measurement provides the number of successfully handled #GGSN#-Initiated #PDP# context update procedures for #QoS# renegotiation. These updates are performed successfully when a positive update #PDP# context response is received from the #SGSN#. Only #QoS# renegotiation procedures are counted.

This measurement provides the number of successfully handled #SGSN#-initiated #PDP# context update procedures. These updates are performed successfully when a positive update #PDP# context response is received from the #GGSN#.

This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful primary #PDP# context Activation procedures per #SGSN-MME# due to cause code 26 (Insufficient resources). The reject can be caused due to, for example, sustained high processor load on one or more #AP#s, or if the hard limit for maximum number of #PDP# contexts is reached.

This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful primary PDP context activation procedures per SGSN due to cause code #27, "Unknown or missing access point name". It is incremented when the SGSN interrogates the DNS resolver and there is a failure, for example, a name error or the default APN of the SGSN is not defined.

This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful primary #PDP# context activation procedures per #SGSN# due to cause code 27 (Unknown or missing access point name), and cause code 28 (Unknown PDP address or PDP type). The counter is incremented when the #SGSN# interrogates the #DNS# resolver and there is a failure - name error or if #APN# (SGSN) is not defined or if requested #PDP# type not sent by #MS# - error.

This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful primary #PDP# context activation procedures per #SGSN# due to cause code 29 (User Authentication Failed). The counter is incremented if the request is rejected by the #GGSN# (#RADIUS#).

This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful PDP context activation procedures per SGSN due to cause code #32, "Service option not supported". It is incremented if the PDP type is not supported or the #NSAPI# is reserved.

This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful #PDP# context activation procedures per #SGSN-MME# due to cause code 32 (Service option not supported), and cause code 33 (Requested Service Option not subscribed). The counter is incremented if the #PDP# Type is not supported, if #NSAPI# is reserved, if the request is denied in the #SGSN-MME# due to subscriber data restriction, or if there are already four active PDP contexts in the SGSN-MME for a MS, and the MS tries to activate another PDP context in the SGSN-MME.
This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful primary #PDP# Context activation procedures per #SGSN# due to cause code 38 (Network failure).
This measurement provides the number of PDP context activation procedures rejected by the SGSN due to the ODB.

This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful primary #PDP# context activation procedures per #SGSN#, due to #PDP# context activation denial, received from the gsmSCF. The counter is incremented when a #CAMEL# release message is received from the gsmSCF.

This measurement provides the number of Create Session Request messages sent to the #SGW# in the #PDP# context activation procedure for #GSM#, that is, the counter is incremented whenever a Create Session Request message is sent to the #SGW#, excluding the retransmission in the #PDP# context activation procedure for #GSM#.

This measurement provides the number of Create Session Response messages with success received from the #SGW# in the #PDP# context activation procedure for #GSM#, that is, the counter is incremented whenever a Create Session Response message is received from the #SGW# in the #PDP# context activation procedure for #GSM#.
This measurement provides the number of APN convertions in the PDP context activation procedure for GSM.
This measurement provides the number of attempted PGW-initiated PDN Deactivation procedures received from the #Serving Gateway#.
This measurement provides the number of successful PGW-initiated PDN Deactivation procedures sent to the #Serving Gateway#.

This measurement provides the number of Modify Bearer Request messages sent to the #SGW# in #GSM#, that is, the counter is incremented whenever a Modify Bearer Request message is sent to the #SGW# excluding the retransmission.

This measurement provides the number of Modify Bearer Response messages with success received from the #SGW# in #GSM#, that is, the counter is incremented whenever a positive Modify Bearer Response message is received from the #SGW#.

This measurement provides the number of attempted Bearer Modification procedures without QoS update initiated by the PDN Gateway. The counter is incremented when the Update Bearer Request message arrives at the SGSN using the S4 interface. This message may contain multiple bearers, each bearer is cumulated to the counter.

This measurement provides the number of successful Bearer Modification procedures without QoS update initiated by the PDN Gateway. The counter is incremented when the Update Bearer Response message is sent to the Serving Gateway. This message may contain multiple bearers. Each bearer with an indication of a successful bearer update is cumulated to the counter.

This measurement provides the number of attempted Bearer Modification procedures with QoS update initiated by the PDN Gateway. The counter is incremented when the Update Bearer Request message arrives at the SGSN using the S4 interface. This message may contain multiple bearers, each bearer is cumulated to the counter.

This measurement provides the number of successful Bearer Modification procedures with QoS update initiated by the PDN Gateway. The counter is incremented when the Update Bearer Response message is sent to the Serving Gateway. This message may contain multiple bearers. Each bearer with an indication of a successful bearer update is cumulated to the counter.

This measurement provides the number of active S4 mode #PDP# contexts in the #GSM# network, that is, the gauge is incremented in the #GSM# network whenever a new S4 mode #PDP# context mode is activated and decremented in the #GSM# network whenever an S4 mode #PDP# context is deactivated.

This measurement provides the number of subscribers in the #GSM# network having an activated S4 mode #PDP# context, that is, subscribers that can send and receive #GPRS# packet data. The gauge is incremented in the #GSM# network when a subscriber activates the first S4 mode #PDP# context and decremented in the #GSM# network when the subscriber deactivates the last S4 mode #PDP# context.

This measurement provides the total number of #PDP# Context Deactivations per #SGSN# of the PDP Contexts that has been active in SGSN. The counter is also incremented when a PDP Context is moved from one system to another (that is #ISC#) and when a PDP Context is moved from one SGSN to another (that is #ISRAU#). A message can handle more than one PDP context, then the TDI-flag is 1.

This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful #PDP# Context Activation procedures per #SGSN-MME#. The counter is incremented when an Activate (Secondary) #PDP# Context Reject or an SM Status message is sent as a response when an Activate (Secondary) #PDP# Context Request is unsuccessful. Action to be taken if the measurement exceeds its supervised threshold: This is an indication of high activation failure rates, typically caused by misconfigured #MS#s using disallowed #APN#s. In this case the resulting cause code is 28 (Unknown #PDP# address or #PDP# type) or 33 (Requested service option not subscribed). If so, check the routines for providing #MS# configuration. #RADIUS# problems are also a common cause of high failure rates. In this case the resulting cause code is 29 (User authentication failed). The alarm can be caused by #GGSN# or #RADIUS# unavailability.

The gprsSmSgsnUnsuccessfulModifications measurement provides the number of unsuccessful #PDP# context modifications per #SGSN-MME#. Action to be taken if the measurement exceeds its supervised threshold: This is an indication of high modification failure rate, typically caused by radio coverage problems or #GGSN# unavailability.

PmGroup.description: This PmGroup defines measurement types within the Session_SM_G_RA area.

MeasurementType.description: This measurement provides the number of attempted primary #PDP# context activation procedures per #RA# within this SGSN. These include the static as well as the dynamic #PDP# addresses. The counter is incremented as the SGSN identifies the message as a RIL3 Activate PDP Context Request message.
This measurement provides the number of successfully completed primary #PDP# context activations per #RA# within this SGSN. For these context activations, the #GGSN# is updated successfully.

PmGroup.description: This PmGroup defines measurement types within the Session_SM_G_U area.

MeasurementType.description: This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful #SM# procedures (#PDP# Context Activation and inter-#SGSN# #RAU# with active #PDP# contexts) per #SGSN# due to the capacity license PDP Context Limit being exceeded.
This measurement provides the number of DNS query attempts with APN-OI-Replacement, while the UE is a home subscriber.
This measurement provides the number of successful DNS query procedures with APN-OI-Replacement, while the UE is a home subscriber.

PmGroup.description: This PmGroup defines measurement types within the Session_SM_RA area.

MeasurementType.description: This measurement provides the number of active PDP contexts per RA within an SGSN. The guage is incremented when a new PDP context is activated and decremented when a PDP context is deactivated. For an RA Update, the old RA indexed gauge is decremented and the new RA indexed gauge is incremented.

PmGroup.description: This PmGroup defines measurement types within the Session_SM_U area.

MeasurementType.description: This measurement provides the number of #APN# redirections to the SGSN default APN per SGSN.
This measurement provides the number of APN redirections to the subscribed APN of the lowest context ID when using EPS subscription data per SGSN.

This measurement provides the number of #APN# redirections to the subscribed APN per SGSN. #Note: If the SGSN default APN included in the subscribed data is used as the negotiated APN, this counter will exclude this scenario. Note#
This measurement provides the number of APN redirections to the subscribed default APN when using EPS subscription data per SGSN.

This measurement provides the number of attempted primary #PDP# context activation procedures. These include the static as well as the dynamic #PDP# addresses. The counter is incremented at the moment when #SGSN# identifies the message as a #RIL#3 Activate #PDP# Context Request message.
MeasurementType.alarmRaiseDefaultLevel: value of 1% of attach limit (hard limit)
MeasurementType.alarmClearDefaultLevel: value of 0.5% of attach limit (hard limit)

MeasurementType.description: This measurement provides the number of attempted primary #PDP# context activation requests where a dynamic #PDP# address is required to be used.
Number of attempted primary #PDP# Context Activation procedures per #SGSN# for home subscribers. Home subscribers are defined by the roaming status parameter during the #IMSI#-series configuration.

This measurement provides the amount of Primary PDP Context Activation messages that are discarded by UE Signaling Control. Incremented when UE Signaling Control activated, and when it identifies a Activate PDP Context Request message during a control period. Applies to WCDMA systems only.
This measurement provides the number of attempted MS-Initiated and Network-Requested Secondary #PDP# context activations.
This measurement provides the number of attempted Network Requested Secondary #PDP# context activations.
This measurement provides the number of Network Requested Secondary #PDP# context activation requests accepted by MS.
This measurement provides the number of #PDP# context that is disconnected by the #GGSN#. A message can handle more than one PDP context, then the TDI-flag is 1.
This measurement provides the number of #PDP# context that is disconnected by the #MS#. A message can handle more than one PDP context, then the TDI-flag is 1.

This measurement provides the number of #PDP# context that is disconnected by the #SGSN#. Note that the counter is incremented according to standard and also when sending "Deactivate PDP Context Request" to the #MS# after an "Error indication" is received from the #GGSN#. A message can handle more than one PDP context, then the TDI-flag is 1.

This measurement provides the number of #PDP# context that is disconnected by the #SGSN# where cause code 38 (Network failure) is sent to the #MS#. A message can handle more than one PDP context, then the TDI-flag is 1.

This measurement provides the number of #PDP# contexts that were deactivated by the #SGSN-MME# with cause code #39, "Reactivation Required". The cause code is sent to the #MS#. One message can handle more PDP contexts if the TDI-flag is 1.
This measurement provides the number of attempted PDP context deactivation procedures triggered by the SGSN due to the ODB.
This measurement provides the number of attempted #MS#-initiated #PDP# context modifications procedures.
This measurement provides the number of attempted #SGSN#-initiated #PDP# context modifications procedures.

This measurement provides the number of #RAB# setup attempts. The counter is incremented according to the number of required RABs setup included in RAB assignment request that is sent to the #RNC# with #IE# 'Setup RAB'.
This measurement provides the number of attempted RAB Modify Request procedures. It is incremented when RAB Modify Request is received.

This measurement provides the number of attempted #GGSN#-initiated #PDP# context update procedures. An Update #PDP# Context Request message can be sent from a #GGSN# to an #SGSN# to renegotiate the #QoS# of a #PDP# context. Only attempts at #QoS# negotiation are counted.

This measurement provides the number of attempted #SGSN#-initiated #PDP# context update procedures. An Update PDP Context Request message is sent from an #SGSN# to a #GGSN# as part of the #GPRS# inter-#SGSN# routing update procedure or the #PDP# context modification procedure. It is used to change the #QoS# and the path. The message is sent by the new #SGSN# at the inter-#SGSN# routing update procedure.
This measurement provides the number of deleted PDP contexts in old SGSN instead of transferring to new SGSN, that is when the T3 tunnel expires.

This measurement provides the number of active #PDP# contexts, that is, the gauge is incremented whenever a new #PDP# context is activated and decremented whenever a #PDP# context is deactivated. Note: The triggering and clearing levels needs to be changed manually or by triggering a manual small restart when the #PDP# capacity license value is changed. Action to be taken if the measurement exceeds its supervised threshold: This is an indication that the #SGSN-MME# is approaching the maximum number of activated #PDP# contexts. Offload the #SGSN-MME#, for example, by moving one or more #RNC#s to a less loaded #SGSN-MME#.
MeasurementType.alarmRaiseDefaultLevel: value of 90 % of the PDP capacity license limit
MeasurementType.alarmClearDefaultLevel: value of 85 % of the PDP capacity license limit

MeasurementType.description: This measurement provides the number of active #PDP# contexts approved for 3G Direct Tunnel, that is, a 3G Direct Tunnel is set up for these PDP contexts when they run payload. Note: This gauge is not supervised, no threshold and clearing level apply.

This measurement provides the number of mobile subscribers with activated #PDP# contexts, that is, subscribers that can send and receive #GPRS# packet data.The gauge is incremented when a subscriber activates the first context and decremented when the subscriber deactivates the last context. Note: The triggering and clearing levels needs to be changed manually or by triggering a manual small restart when the #PDP# capacity license value is changed.
MeasurementType.alarmRaiseDefaultLevel: value of 90 % of the PDP capacity license limit
MeasurementType.alarmClearDefaultLevel: value of 85 % of the PDP capacity license limit

MeasurementType.description: This measurement provides the number of PDP contexts deactivated by the old SGSN after the contexts were transferred to the new SGSN. The reason is that the old SGSN aborted the ISRAU procedure when the MS re-entered the old SGSN's service area prior to the old SGSN receiving a CANCEL LOCATION message from the HLR.
This measurement provides the number of successfully completed primary #PDP# context activations. For these context activations, the #GGSN# is updated successfully.
This measurement provides the number of successfully completed primary #PDP# context activations where a dynamic #PDP# address is used.
Number of successful primary #PDP# Context Activation procedures per #SGSN# for home subscribers. Home subscribers are defined by the roaming status parameter during the #IMSI#-series configuration.
This measurement provides the number of successfully completed MS-Initiated and Network-Requested Secondary #PDP# context activations.
This measurement provides the number of successfully completed Network Requested Secondary #PDP# context activations.

This measurement provides the number of successfully handled #PDP# context deactivations initiated by the #GGSN#. For these context deactivations, the #MS# has accepted the #PDP# context deactivation. A message can handle more than one PDP context, then the TDI-flag is 1.

This measurement provides the number of successfully completed #PDP# context deactivations. For these context deactivations, the #GGSN# is updated successfully (that is, deletion of the #PDP# context). A message can handle more than one PDP context, then the TDI-flag is 1.

This measurement provides the number of successfully handled #PDP# context deactivations initiated by the #SGSN#. Note that the counter is incremented according to standard and also when receiving "Delete PDP Context Response" from the #GGSN# for the cases when no "Deactivate PDP Context Response" can be received from the #MS# since no "Deactivate PDP Context Request" was sent to the #MS#. A message can handle more than one PDP context, then the TDI-flag is 1.

This measurement provides the number of successfully handled #MS#-initiated #PDP# context modifications procedures. These modifications are performed successfully when a Modify PDP Context Accept message is sent to the #MS#.

This measurement provides the number of successfully handled #SGSN#-initiated #PDP# context modifications procedures. These modifications are performed successfully when a positive Modify PDP Context Accept message is received from the #MS#.
This measurement provides the number of successful #RAB# setups. It is incremented when a RAB Assignment Response message is received, indicating successful #RAB# setup.

This measurement provides the number of successfully handled #GGSN#-Initiated #PDP# context update procedures for #QoS# renegotiation. These updates are performed successfully when a positive update #PDP# context response is received from the #SGSN#. Only #QoS# renegotiation procedures are counted.

This measurement provides the number of successfully handled #SGSN#-initiated #PDP# context update procedures. These updates are performed successfully when a positive update #PDP# context response is received from the #GGSN#.

This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful #PDP# Context Activation procedures per #SGSN-MME#. The counter is incremented when an Activate (Secondary) #PDP# Context Reject or an SM Status message is sent as a response if an Activate (Secondary) #PDP# Context Request is unsuccessful. Action to be taken if the measurement exceeds its supervised threshold: This is an indication of high activation failure rates, typically caused by misconfigured #MS#s using disallowed #APN#s. In this case the resulting cause code is 28 (Unknown #PDP# address or #PDP# type) or 33 (Requested service option not subscribed). If so, check the routines for providing #MS# configuration. #RADIUS# problems are also a common cause of high failure rates. In this case the resulting cause code is 29 (User authentication failed). The alarm can be caused by #GGSN# or #RADIUS# unavailability.

This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful primary #PDP# context Activation procedures per #SGSN-MME# due to cause code 26 (Insufficient resources). The reject can be caused due to, for example, sustained high processor load on one or more #AP#s, or if the hard limit for maximum number of #PDP# contexts is reached.

This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful primary PDP context activation procedures per SGSN due to cause code #27, "Unknown or missing access point name". It is incremented when the SGSN interrogates the DNS resolver and there is a failure, for example, a name error or the default APN of the SGSN is not defined.

This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful primary #PDP# context activation procedures per #SGSN# due to cause code 27 (Unknown or missing access point name), and cause code 28 (Unknown PDP address or PDP type). The counter is incremented when the #SGSN# interrogates the #DNS# resolver and there is a failure - name error or if #APN# (SGSN) is not defined or if requested #PDP# type not sent by #MS# - error.

This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful primary #PDP# context activation procedures per #SGSN# due to cause code 29 (User Authentication Failed). The counter is incremented if the request is rejected by the #GGSN# (#RADIUS#).

This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful PDP context activation procedures per SGSN due to cause code #32, "Service option not supported". It is incremented if the PDP type is not supported or the #NSAPI# is reserved.

This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful #PDP# Context activation procedures per #SGSN-MME# due to cause code 32 (Service option not supported), and cause code 33 (Requested Service Option not subscribed). The counter is incremented if the #PDP# Type is not supported, if #NSAPI# is reserved or if the request is denied in the #SGSN-MME# due to subscriber data restriction.
This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful primary #PDP# context activation procedures per #SGSN# due to cause code 38 (Network failure).
This measurement provides the number of PDP context activation procedures rejected by the SGSN due to the ODB.

This measurement provides the number of unsuccessful primary #PDP# context activation procedures per #SGSN#, due to PDP context activation denial, received from the gsmSCF. The counter is incremented when a CAMEL release message is received from the gsmSCF.

This measurement provides the number of Create Session Request messages sent to the SGW in WCDMA, that is, the counter is incremented whenever a Create Session Request message is sent to the SGW excluding the retransmission.

This measurement provides the number of Create Session Response messages received from the SGW with success in WCDMA, that is, the counter is incremented whenever a Create Session Response message is received from the SGW.
For each attempted Network Requested Secondary #PDP# Context Activation Procedure using S4, this counter is incremented with the number of bearers included in the Create Bearer Request.

For each attempted Network Requested Secondary #PDP# Context Activation Procedure using S4, this counter is incremented with the number of successfully activated bearers included in the Create Bearer Response.
This measurement provides the number of APN convertions in the PDP context activation procedure for UMTS.

This measurement provides the amount of Activate PDP Context Request messages that are controlled by the UE Signaling Control feature with the detach action. The counter applies only when the UE Signaling Control feature is activated in the Measurement and Control mode. The counter is increased whenever an Activate PDP Context Request message is identified and controlled by UE Signaling Control with the detach action during a control period.

This measurement provides the amount of Activate PDP Context Request messages that are controlled by the UE Signaling Control feature with the reject action. The counter applies only when the UE Signaling Control feature is activated in the Measurement and Control mode. The counter is increased whenever an Activate PDP Context Request message is identified and controlled by UE Signaling Control with the reject action during a control period.

This measurement provides the number of EPS bearers with QoS mismatch between the S4-SGSN and PGW. It is incremented if the S4-SGSN does not receive a PGW-initiated QoS modification within a certain time after an EPS bearer has been downgraded due to QoS policy map during RAU from the S4-SGSN/MME to the S4-SGSN or handover from the MME to the S4-SGSN.

This measurement provides the number of attempted #MS#-Initiated Dedicated Bearer Deactivation Procedures over the S4 interface. The value is increased whenever the S4-#SGSN# receives a Deactivate PDP Context Request message from the MS.

This measurement provides the number of successful #MS#-Initiated Dedicated Bearer Deactivation Procedures over the S4 interface. The value is increased when the #S4-SGSN# sends a Deactivate PDP Context Accept message to the #MS#.

This measurement provides the number of bearers included in the Delete Bearer Request. The value is increased whenever a Delete Bearer Request is sent during each attempted #MS#-, #SGSN#-, or #PGW#-initiated Dedicated Bearer Deactivation Procedure over the S4 interface.

This measurement provides the number of successfully deactivated bears during each #MS#-, #SGSN#-, or #PGW#-initiated Dedicated Bearer Deactivation Procedure over the S4 interface. The value is increased whenever a bearer is deactivated in the Delete Bearer Response message.
This measurement provides the number of attempted PGW-initiated PDN Deactivation procedures received from the #Serving Gateway#.
This measurement provides the number of successful PGW-initiated PDN Deactivation procedures sent to the #Serving Gateway#.

This measurement provides the number of bearers included in the Delete Bearer Command. The value is increased whenever a Delete Bearer Command is sent during each attempted #MS#- or #SGSN#-initiated Dedicated Bearer Deactivation Procedure over the S4 interface.

This measurement provides the number of Modify Bearer Command messages sent to the SGW for WCDMA access. The measured data of this counter is incremented when a Modify Bearer Command message is sent to the SGW, excluding the retransmission.

This measurement provides the number of successful Modify Bearer Command responses (Update Bearer Request messages) received from the SGW for WCDMA access. The measured data of this counter is incremented when an Update Bearer Request message is received from the SGW.

This measurement provides the number of Modify Bearer Request messages sent to the #SGW# in #WCDMA#, that is, the counter is incremented whenever a Modify Bearer Request message is sent to the #SGW# excluding the retransmission.

This measurement provides the number of Modify Bearer Response messages with success received from the #SGW# in #WCDMA#, that is, the counter is incremented whenever a positive Modify Bearer Response message is received from the #SGW#.

This measurement provides the number of attempted Bearer Modification procedures without QoS update initiated by the PDN Gateway. The counter is incremented when the Update Bearer Request message arrives at the SGSN using the S4 interface. This message may contain multiple bearers, each bearer is cumulated to the counter.

This measurement provides the number of successful Bearer Modification procedures without QoS update initiated by the PDN Gateway. The counter is incremented when the Update Bearer Response message is sent to the Serving Gateway. This message may contain multiple bearers. Each bearer with an indication of a successful bearer update is cumulated to the counter.

This measurement provides the number of attempted Bearer Modification procedures with QoS update initiated by the PDN Gateway. The counter is incremented when the Update Bearer Request message arrives at the SGSN using the S4 interface. This message may contain multiple bearers, each bearer is cumulated to the counter.

This measurement provides the number of successful Bearer Modification procedures with QoS update initiated by the PDN Gateway. The counter is incremented when the Update Bearer Response message is sent to the Serving Gateway. This message may contain multiple bearers. Each bearer with an indication of a successful bearer update is cumulated to the counter.

This measurement provides the number of active S4 mode PDP contexts in WCDMA network, that is, the gauge is incremented in WCDMA whenever a new PDP context of S4 mode is activated and decremented in WCDMA whenever a PDP context of S4 mode is deactivated.

This measurement provides the number of active bearers approved for 3G Direct Tunnel on the SGSN supporting the S4 interface with #UMTS# access, that is, a 3G Direct Tunnel is set up for these bearers.

This measurement provides the number of active default #EPS# bearers in S4-SGSN, that is, the gauge is incremented when a new default #EPS# bearer is activated and decremented when a default #EPS# bearer is deactivated in S4-SGSN.

This measurement provides the number of subscribers in WCDMA network having an activated PDP context of S4 mode, that is subscribers that can send and receive GPRS packet data. The gauge is incremented in WCDMA network when a subscriber activates the first context of S4 mode and decremented in WCDMA network when the subscriber deactivates the last context of S4 mode.

This measurement provides the number of times the tunnel mode is switched from being of one tunnel (or direct tunnel) to two-tunnel. Note: This measurement is only applicable for the tunnel switch due to Service Request Frequency.

This measurement provides the number of times the tunnel mode is switched from being of two-tunnels to one tunnel (or direct tunnel). Note: This measurement is only applicable for the tunnel switch due to Service Request Frequency.

This measurement provides the number of Create Session Request messages sent to the restarted SGW in the Gateway Restoration procedure for WCDMA S4-SGSN. The counter does not increase if the Create Session Request message is retransmitted.
This measurement provides the number of Create Session Response messages with "Accept" types of cause values received from the SGW in the Gateway Restoration procedure for WCDMA S4-SGSN.

PmGroup.description: This PmGroup defines measurement types within the Session_SM_U_RA area.

MeasurementType.description: This measurement provides the number of attempted primary #PDP# context activation procedures per #RA# within this SGSN. These include the static as well as the dynamic #PDP# addresses. The counter is incremented as the SGSN identifies the message as a RIL3 Activate PDP Context Request message.
This measurement provides the number of successfully completed primary #PDP# context activations per #RA# within this SGSN. For these context activations, the #GGSN# is updated successfully.

PmGroup.description: This PmGroup defines measurement types within the SubscriberManagement_MM area.

MeasurementType.description: This measurement provides the number of attempted Current Location requests from the HSS. It increases whenever an Insert Subscriber Data Request message with the IDR-flags IE indicating Current Location Request is received from the HSS.

This measurement provides the number of attempted EPS Location Information requests from the HSS. It increases whenever an Insert Subscriber Data Request message with the IDR-flags IE indicating EPS Location Information Request is received from the HSS.

This measurement provides the number of attempted Local Time Zone requests from the HSS. It increases whenever an Insert Subscriber Data Request message with the IDR-flags IE indicating Local Time Zone Request is received from the HSS.

This measurement provides the number of attempted UE Reachability requests from the HSS. It increases whenever an Insert Subscriber Data Request message with the IDR-flags IE indicating UE Reachability Request is received from the HSS.

This measurement provides the number of attempted EPS User State requests from the HSS. It increases whenever an Insert Subscriber Data Request message with the IDR-flags IE indicating EPS User State Request is received from the HSS.

PmGroup.description: This PmGroup defines measurement types within the SubscriberManagement_SUB area.

MeasurementType.description: This measurement provides the number of attempted delete subscriber data requests received from the HSS.
This measurement provides the number of attempted insert subscriber data requests received from the HSS.

PmGroup.description: This PmGroup defines measurement types within the SystemResource_IPPayload_G area.

MeasurementType.description: This measurement provides the number of deleted IP packets due to memory allocation failure.

PmGroup.description: This PmGroup defines measurement types within the SystemResource_IPPayload_U area.

MeasurementType.description: This measurement provides the number of deleted IP packets due to memory allocation failure.

PmGroup.description: This PmGroup defines measurement types within the SystemResource_PIU area.

MeasurementType.description: This measurement shows the current #CPU# usage per group of cores running AP functionality on a #GEP# #PIU#. The value is the average #CPU# load measured on a per minute basis. #Note:This counter is only applicable on MkVIII.Note# Action to be taken if the measurement exceeds its supervised threshold: If there is an indication of high #CPU# load for a longer time period then it might be necessary to troubleshoot why there is a high #CPU# load. One remedy could be to offload the #SGSN-MME#, for example, by reconfiguring and moving part of the traffic to another interface, or by moving one or more #BSC#s, #RNC#s or #eNodeB#s to a less loaded #SGSN-MME#. Overload can also occur in recovery phase, for example, after a restart. In this case no actions are required.

This measurement shows the current #CPU# usage per processor. This measurement is applicable for all boards except #CMXB#s. The value is the average #CPU# load measured on a per minute basis. Action to be taken if the measurement exceeds its supervised threshold: If there is an indication of high #CPU# load for a longer time period then it might be necessary to troubleshoot why there is a high #CPU# load. One remedy could be to offload the #SGSN-MME#, for example, by reconfiguring and moving part of the traffic to another interface, or by moving one or more #BSC#s, #RNC#s or #eNodeB#s to a less loaded #SGSN-MME#. Overload can also occur in recovery phase, for example, after a restart.In this case no actions are required.

This measurement shows the current memory usage per processor. This measurement is applicable for all boards except #CMXB#s. The value is the average memory consumption measured on a per minute basis. Action to be taken if the measurement exceeds its supervised threshold: If there is an indication of high memory usage for a long time period then it might be necessary to troubleshoot why there is a high memory usage.

This measurement shows the current #CPU# usage per group of cores running SS7/SCTP DP functionality on ar #GEP# #PIU#. The value is the average #CPU# load measured on a per minute basis. #Note:This counter is only applicable on MkVIII.Note# Action to be taken if the measurement exceeds its supervised threshold: If there is an indication of high #CPU# load for a longer time period then it might be necessary to troubleshoot why there is a high #CPU# load. One remedy could be to offload the #SGSN-MME#, for example, by reconfiguring and moving part of the traffic to another interface, or by moving one or more #BSC#s, #RNC#s or #eNodeB#s to a less loaded #SGSN-MME#. Overload can also occur in recovery phase, for example, after a restart. In this case no actions are required.

PmGroup.description: This PmGroup defines measurement types within the SystemResource_PayloadDPInstance area.

MeasurementType.description: This measurement shows the current #CPU# usage per group of cores running Payload DP functionality on a #GEP# #PIU#. The value is the max #CPU# load measured on a per minute basis. #Note:This counter is only applicable on MkVIII.Note# Action to be taken if the measurement exceeds its supervised threshold: If there is an indication of high #CPU# load for a longer time period then it might be necessary to troubleshoot why there is a high #CPU# load. One remedy could be to offload the #SGSN-MME#, for example, by reconfiguring and moving part of the traffic to another interface, or by moving one or more #BSC#s, #RNC#s or #eNodeB#s to a less loaded #SGSN-MME#. Overload can also occur in recovery phase, for example, after a restart. In this case no actions are required.

PmGroup.description: This PmGroup defines measurement types within the UeSecurity_E area.

MeasurementType.description: This measurement provides the number of attempted #EPS# authentication challenges that are started within this #MME# area for a subscriber using a #USIM#.

This measurement provides the number of attempted Security Mode Control procedures started within this #MME# area, for a subscriber using a #USIM#. The resending of the Security Mode Command message is not counted.
This measurement provides the number of Authentication Reject messages sent by the MME during the Attach procedure. The authentication rejection due to timeout (T3460) is not counted.

This measurement provides the number of failed Authentication Information Retrieval procedures over the S6a interface with cause code 5001. The counter is increased whenever the MME receives an Authentication Information Answer message with cause code 5001 (User unkown).

This measurement provides the number of failed Authentication Information Retrieval procedures over the S6a interface with cause code 5420. The counter is increased whenever the MME receives an Authentication Information Answer message with cause code 5420 (Unkown EPS subscription).

This measurement provides the number of authentication failures due to cause code 20 (MAC failure). The counter is increased whenever the UE detects an incorrect authentication parameter in the Authentication Request message.
This measurement provides the number of authentication failures due to cause code 21 (Sync failure). The counter is increased whenever the UE detects an incorrect SQN or a SQN is out of range.

This measurement provides the number of authentication failures due to cause code 26 (Non-EPS authentication unacceptable). The counter is increased whenever the UE detects an incorrect authentication parameter in the Authentication Request message.
This measurement provides the number of attempted Identification Request procedures initiated by the #MME#.
This measurement provides the number of successful Identification procedures initiated by the #MME#.
This measurement provides the number of attempted Identity Request procedures initiated by the #MME#.
This measurement provides the number of successful Identity procedures initiated by the #MME#.
This measurement provides the number of successful #EPS# authentication challenges that are started within this #MME# area for a subscriber using a #USIM#.
This measurement provides the number of successful Security Mode Control procedures within this #MME# area, for a subscriber using a #USIM#.
This measurement provides the number of Authentication Reject messages sent by the MME during the Inter-MME TAU procedure. The authentication rejection due to timeout (T3460) is not counted.

This measurement provides the number of authentication reject messages sent by the MME during the inter-node ISC TAU procedures (with RAT change). The authentication rejection due to (T3460) timeout is not counted.

This measurement provides the number of authentication reject messages sent by the MME during the intra-node ISC TAU procedures (with RAT change). The authentication rejection due to (T3460) timeout is not counted.

PmGroup.description: This PmGroup defines measurement types within the UeSecurity_G area.

MeasurementType.description: This measurement provides the number of authentication procedures that are started within this #SGSN# area for a subscriber using a #SIM#. Valid for subscribers (#GSM# and #UMTS#) located within #GSM# Access System.

This measurement provides the number of authentication procedures that are started within this #SGSN# area for a subscriber using a #USIM#. Valid for #UMTS# subscribers located within #GSM# Access Systems.

This measurement provides the number of SGSN Context Request messages or Context Request messages received from a partner (new) SGSN/MME for a subscriber de-registering from this SGSN. It is incremented at receipt of the "#SGSN# Context Request" message or "Context Request" message from the new #SGSN#/MME.

This measurement provides the number of #SGSN# Context Request messages or Context Request messages sent to a partner (previous) #SGSN#/MME for subscribers registering afresh in this #SGSN#. Resendings are also counted. It is incremented at transmission of the "#SGSN# Context Request" message or "Context Request" message to the previous #SGSN#/MME.
This measurement provides the number of attempted Identity Request procedures initiated by this #SGSN#.
This measurement provides the number of ciphering and Authentication failures within this #SGSN# area.

This measurement provides the number of successful authentication procedures within this #SGSN# area, for a subscriber using a #SIM#. Valid for subscribers (#GSM# and #UMTS#) located within #GSM# Access System.

This measurement provides the number of successful authentication procedures within this #SGSN# area, for a subscriber using a #USIM#. Valid for #UMTS# subscribers located within #GSM# Access Systems.

This measurement provides the number of successfully replied #SGSN# Context Request messages or Context Request messages that were sent to a partner (previous) #SGSN#/MME. It is incremented at receipt of the "#SGSN# Context Response" message or "Context Response" message from the previous #SGSN#/MME.
This measurement provides the number of successfully completed Identity Request procedures initiated by this #SGSN#.

PmGroup.description: This PmGroup defines measurement types within the UeSecurity_Hlr area.

MeasurementType.description: This measurement provides the number of attempted #MAP# requests for authentication sets sent to the #HLR# by SGSN. Note! All #MAP# versions are counted.
This measurement provides the number of successful #MAP# requests for authentication sets that were sent to the #HLR#. Note! All #MAP# versions are counted.
This measurement provides the number of empty responses to the #MAP# request for authentication sets that were sent to the #HLR#. Note! All #MAP# versions are counted.

PmGroup.description: This PmGroup defines measurement types within the UeSecurity_Hss area.

MeasurementType.description: This measurement provides the number of attempted S6a/S6d Authentication Information Retrieval procedures in the SGSN/MME.
This measurement provides the number of successful S6a/S6d Authentication Information Retrieval procedures in the SGSN/MME.

PmGroup.description: This PmGroup defines measurement types within the UeSecurity_SgsnFunction area.

MeasurementType.description: This measurement provides the number of authentication procedures that are started within this #SGSN# area.
This measurement provides the number of successful authentication procedures within this #SGSN# area.

PmGroup.description: This PmGroup defines measurement types within the UeSecurity_U area.

MeasurementType.description: This measurement provides the number of authentication procedures that are started within this #SGSN# area for a subscriber using a #SIM#. Valid for #GSM# subscribers located within #UMTS# Access System.

This measurement provides the number of authentication procedures that are started within this #SGSN# area for a subscriber using a #USIM#. Valid for #UMTS# subscribers located within #UMTS# Access Systems.

This measurement provides the number of SGSN context requests or context requests received from a partner (new) SGSN/MME for a subscriber de-registering from this SGSN. It is incremented at receipt of the "#SGSN# Context Request" message or "Context Request" message from the new #SGSN#/MME.

This measurement provides the number of #SGSN# context requests or context requests sent to a partner (previous) #SGSN#/MME for subscribers registering afresh in this #SGSN#. Resendings are also counted. It is incremented at transmission of the "#SGSN# Context Request" message or "Context Request" message to the previous #SGSN#/MME.
This measurement provides the number of attempted Identity Request procedures initiated by this #SGSN#.
This measurement provides the number of security mode control procedures started by the #SGSN#.
This measurement provides the number of ciphering and Authentication failures within this #SGSN# area.
This measurement provides the number of successful authentication procedures within this #SGSN# area, for a subscriber using a #SIM#. Valid for #GSM# subscribers located within #UMTS# Access System.

This measurement provides the number of successful authentication procedures within this #SGSN# area, for a subscriber using a #USIM#. Valid for #UMTS# subscribers located within #UMTS# Access Systems.

This measurement provides the number of successfully replied #SGSN# context requests or context requests that were sent to a partner (previous) #SGSN#/MME. It is incremented at receipt of the "#SGSN# Context Response" message or "Context Response" message from the previous #SGSN#/MME.
This measurement provides the number of successfully completed Identity Request procedures initiated by this #SGSN#.

This measurement provides the number of successful security mode procedures. The security mode command response from #MS# starts the uplink integrity protection (and possible ciphering). All following messages sent from the MS are integrity protected (and possibly ciphered).

PmGroup.description: This PmGroup defines measurement types within the UserEquipment_Gf area.

MeasurementType.description: This measurement provides the number of black list answers received from the #EIR#. Note that the counter contains a total count for both #GSM# and #WCDMA# System.
This measurement provides the number of check #IMEI# requests sent to the #EIR#. Note that the counter contains a total count for both #GSM# and #WCDMA# System.
This measurement provides the number of gray list answers received from the #EIR#. Note that the counter contains a total count for both #GSM# and #WCDMA# System.
This measurement provides the number of unknown #IMEI# answers received from the #EIR#.Note that the counter contains a total count for both #GSM# and #WCDMA# System.
This measurement provides the number of white list answers received from the #EIR#. Note that the counter contains a total count for both #GSM# and #WCDMA# System.

PmGroup.description: This PmGroup defines measurement types within the UserEquipment_S13 area.

MeasurementType.description: This measurement provides the number of requests for #IMEI# Check sent to the #EIR# through the S13 interface.
This measurement provides the number of answers with equipment status set to BLACKLISTED received from the #EIR# through the S13 interface.
This measurement provides the number of answers with equipment status set to GREYLISTED received from the #EIR# through the S13 interface.
This measurement provides the number of answers indicating that the #ME# is unknown to the #EIR#.
This measurement provides the number of answers with equipment status set to WHITELISTED received from the #EIR# through the S13 interface.

PmGroup.description: This PmGroup defines measurement types within the WCDMA_GSM_ISYSC area.

MeasurementType.description: Number of attempted intra-#SGSN# inter-system changes from #GSM# to #WCDMA# System.
Number of attempted intra-#SGSN# inter-system changes from #WCDMA# System to #GSM#.
Number of successful intra-#SGSN# inter-system changes from #GSM# to #WCDMA# System.
Number of successful intra-#SGSN# inter-system changes from #WCDMA# System to #GSM#.

PmGroup.description: This PmGroup defines measurement types within the WIFI area.

MeasurementType.description: This measurement provides the number of EAB WIFI Access Decision Request messages sent from the MME to the eNodeB over the S1-MME interface. This counter is incremented each time an EAB WIFI Access Decision Request message is sent by the MME.

This measurement provides the number of successful EAB WIFI Access Decision Response messages received from the eNodeB. This counter is incremented each time a successful EAB WIFI Access Decision Response message is received from the eNodeB.

This measurement provides the number of Access Request messages received from the Wi-Fi Controller over the U2 interface. This counter is incremented each time an Access Request message is received from the Wi-Fi Controller.

This measurement provides the number of Access Response messages sent from the MME to the Wi-Fi Controller. This counter is incremented each time a successful Access Response message is sent by the MME.

This measurement provides the number of Estimate Request messages received from the Wi-Fi Controller over the U2 interface. This counter is incremented each time an Estimate Request message is received from the Wi-Fi Controller.

This measurement provides the number of Estimate Response messages sent from the MME to the Wi-Fi Controller. This counter is incremented each time a successful Estimate Response message is sent by the MME.

This measurement provides the number of First Update Indication messages received from the Wi-Fi UE Locator over the U1a interface. This counter is incremented each time a First Update Indication message is received from the Wi-Fi UE Locator.

This measurement provides the number of EAB Throughput Estimation Request messages sent from the MME to the eNodeB over the S1-MME interface. This counter is incremented each time an EAB Throughput Estimation Request message is sent by the MME.

This measurement provides the number of successful EAB Throughput Estimation Response messages received from the eNodeB. This counter is incremented each time when the MME receives an EAB Throughput Estimation Response message from the eNodeB.

This measurement provides the number of UE Location Update messages sent to the Wi-Fi UE Locator over the U1a interface. This counter is incremented each time a UE Location Update message is sent to the Wi-Fi UE Locator.

PmGroup.description: This PmGroup defines measurement types within the eMBMS area.

MeasurementType.description: This measurement provides the number of MBMS Session Start Request messages sent to the MCEs over the M3 interface, that is, the counter is incremented whenever an MBMS Session Start Request message is sent to the MCEs.

This measurement provides the number of MBMS Session Start Response messages with success received from the MCEs over the M3 interface, that is, the counter is incremented whenever a positive MBMS Session Start Response message is received from an MCE.

This measurement provides the number of MBMS Session Stop Request messages sent to the MCEs over the M3 interface, that is, the counter is incremented whenever an MBMS Session Stop Request message is sent to the MCEs.

This measurement provides the number of MBMS Session Stop Response messages with success received from the MCEs over the M3 interface, that is, the counter is incremented whenever a MBMS Session Stop Response message with success is received from an MCE.
This measurement provides the number of active eMBMS sessions in the MME.
This measurement provides the number of currently disconnected MCEs.

This measurement provides the number of MBMS Session Start Request messages received from the MBMS-GW over the Sm interface, that is, the counter is incremented whenever an MBMS Session Start Request message is received from the MBMS-GW.

This measurement provides the number of MBMS Session Start Response messages with success sent to the MBMS-GW over the Sm interface, that is, the counter is incremented whenever a MBMS Session Start Response message with success is sent to the MBMS-GW.

This measurement provides the number of MBMS Session Stop Request messages received from the MBMS-GW over the Sm interface, that is, the counter is incremented whenever an MBMS Session Stop Request message is received from the MBMS-GW.

This measurement provides the number of MBMS Session Stop Response messages with success sent to the MBMS-GW over the Sm interface, that is, the counter is incremented whenever a MBMS Session Stop Response message with success is sent to the MBMS-GW.
